## Exact Claim

A practice completes a stage not only by working, but by changing what may guide the next action. The audit variable is a two-axis pair: whether the method validates or undermines its own use, and where post-threshold authority is retained, laid down, embodied, handed to teacher or community, held by grace or vow, or refused as possession. The modern risk is that a once-helpful method becomes a private judge of worth, shame, and self-surveillance.

## Claim Units

- Stage completion is defined by a change in permitted guidance, not merely by a successful experience.
- Boundary operation and post-threshold custody should be coded together.
- Post-method authority may be retained, released, embodied, externally held, grace-held, vow-held, conduct-held, or refused.
- A method can become a private judge for achievement-driven practitioners.
- The practice fit is bounded: it targets achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, and perfectionistic self-monitoring, not acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, or beginners needing simple consistency.

## Primary Text Close Read

Sources:
- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html; Heart Sutra no attainment with reliance on prajnaparamita, https://www.fgsitc.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Heart-Sutra-2016.pdf
