observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:7:Status: draft
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:12:The keep, release, embody model silently assumes that the practitioner provisionally owns the method and that there is an after in which custody of the result can be decided. Radical Other Power and practice-realization break those assumptions: in Shinran's jinen honi the practitioner never owns the method, trust, or result, while in Dogen's shusho-itto there is no discrete after outside practice. Therefore the custody model is bounded, and for depleted over-managing people the prompt to decide what to keep, release, or embody can become one more burden.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:18:- Shinran's Other Power refuses practitioner ownership, calculation, and self-generated entrusting.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:26:- Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:27:- Dogen, Bendowa and shusho-itto practice-realization sources, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:29:Structural observation: Shinran relocates efficacy to Other Power and warns against calculation, so the practitioner is not the owner who later decides how to carry the method. Dogen's practice-realization collapses the gap between practice and verification, so a later custody decision is not the native shape of the path. These are strong boundary cases against a universal after-use grid, but they do not eliminate all guidance: Shin still has nembutsu, warnings, and entrusting language, and Soto still has zazen, discipline, teacher correction, and conduct.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:31:Secondary literature gap: This audit did not read Japanese sources, Dogen commentarial scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Pargament's full agency-style work, or ethnographic practitioner accounts. It also did not verify whether other traditions with inherited practice, ritual-first formation, or apophatic unsaying similarly refuse the ownership-and-after assumptions.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:33:Risk of overread: Moderate to high. The claim may exaggerate refusal into absence. Other Power and practice-realization may not abolish all custody questions; they may relocate custody to vow, teacher, text, sangha, conduct, or practice itself. The human-condition claim may also overgeneralize depletion, since some burned-out people need structure and accountability rather than non-audit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:37:- Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power natural working of the primal vow
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:38:- Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act practicer Other Power self power
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:39:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto verification outside practice
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:42:- Pargament deferring religious coping style agency God control
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:48:- Internal Lumenary audit, You cannot release what you never held, https://local/reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json: overlap: Extremely close. Both argue that release teaching applies to active-voice result-ownership, while Other Power, practice-realization, and no-attainment sources strain or refuse the release frame.; difference: The current idea emphasizes non-ownership and no-after as scope conditions and adds the No-Audit Check for depleted over-managers.; novelty impact: Major internal downgrade. This is best treated as a sibling consolidation, not a separate discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:49:- Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/: overlap: Very close for the non-ownership claim: natural working and Other Power oppose practicer calculation and self-generated control.; difference: The candidate uses Shinran as a scope condition for a comparative after-use model and as a modern caution for over-management.; novelty impact: Major downgrade for the theological structure. The contribution is a boundary application, not a discovery of non-ownership.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:50:- Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/: overlap: Very close for denying nembutsu as the practitioner's self-powered good act or possessed practice.; difference: The candidate frames that denial as a failure of keep, release, embody categories.; novelty impact: Downgrades to renamed or extended. The primary text already contains the core refusal of ownership.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:52:- Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles: overlap: Close for agency relocation away from the individual self and toward divine action, especially deferring and collaborative modes.; difference: Pargament studies coping style and control attribution, not method-completion temporality or practitioner ownership as scope conditions.; novelty impact: Reduces novelty of the agency claim. The candidate must show predictive gain beyond deferring, collaborative, and self-directing agency models.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:57:Unlike Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, Pargament's agency styles, burnout rumination literature, and prior Lumenary release and custody models, this idea's possible contribution is an explicit scope test: before applying keep, release, or embody guidance, first ask whether the tradition grants provisional practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and whether the person has enough agency to benefit from a custody prompt.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:63:Why it strains the model: If nembutsu, zazen, teacher correction, vows, forms, and ordinary conduct function as retained or embodied methods, then the custody model is not abolished. It is relocated from self-ownership to vow, practice, teacher, community, or form. The boundary claim would then be overstated.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:69:- If: Ownership and after are true scope conditions for after-use models. Then: Blind coders can identify texts that grant practitioner ownership and discrete completion separately from texts that relocate or refuse those assumptions, and those codes predict held-out warning and repair patterns. Weakens if: Coders cannot separate refusal from relocation, or retain, release, embody categories work equally well across Shinran, Dogen, Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, apophatic Christian, and Sufi sources. Test surface: Split-source corpus coding with entry passages, doctrinal passages, and held-out manuals or practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:79:- Theravada teachers familiar with raft and non-clinging instructions
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:90:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as Other Power, practice-realization, grace, surrender, non-calculation, or non-gaining mind, and that the no-audit prompt is simply rest from rumination or basic clinical caution.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:110:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.28. The non-ownership and no-after structures are well established in Shinran and Dogen, and the core Lumenary comparison is already present in the recent audit of You cannot release what you never held. The modern caution overlaps with known rumination, perfectionism, and burnout risks. Human-condition fit is strong for depleted over-managers, caregivers, founders, professionals, students, and serious practitioners who turn even rest into performance. It is not for people who need planning, accountability, medication, therapy, social support, or material workload reduction, nor for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, or responsibility avoidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md:117:- Close-read Shinran's Japanese terms around jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen on shusho-itto and non-gaining, and practitioner manuals where concrete guidance appears.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Keeps the idea at extended. It can only rise if voice coding predicts warnings, confusion, and repair better than self-power, Other Power, Pargament agency style, teacher style, and clinical-risk baselines.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If most actual paths shift voices by stage, role, and context, then active versus middle voice will not sort traditions or predict guidance. Pure Land practitioners still say the nembutsu, Zen practitioners still sit, Christian grace traditions still discipline attention, and high-striving nondual practitioners may still benefit from release advice despite no-owner doctrine."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:11:    "Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra break the grid by rejecting an active owner who finishes and assigns custody.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:36:      "test_surface": "Split-source codebook tested on MN 22, Tannisho, Dogen, Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, Christian grace texts, and practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:37:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Custody values, tradition identity, teacher style, institution type, or Pargament agency styles predict guidance as well as or better than voice coding."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:40:      "expected_observation": "Coders will overuse embodied-without-ownership for Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, Dzogchen, apophasis, and other hard cases, with low inter-rater reliability and weak prediction of warnings.",
