reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:87:      "source": "G. Victor Sogen Hori, Koan and Kensho in the Rinzai Zen Curriculum, search-accessible copy, https://docslib.org/doc/1302437/the-koan-is-said-to-pose-to-the-ze-n-practitione-r-a-parado-x-unsolvabl-e-by-the-rational-intellectualizing-mind"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:98:    "Close-read Mandukya, Heart Sutra, MN 22, Vigrahavyavartani 29, and Hori's koan curriculum before treating the three types as stable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:99:    "Search further for upaya, raft, ladder, thorn-removes-thorn, Gelassenheit, fana and baqa, rang grol, and practice-realization as exact structural near-neighbors.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:105:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say every serious path already uses all three stages, or identify the model as a familiar upaya, raft, ladder, no-thesis, fana, or Gelassenheit pattern with new labels.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:127:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact three-type typology of contemplative methods as confirming, canceling, and dissolving at completion. But the self-canceling portion has very strong prior art in Nagarjuna, Wittgenstein ladder readings, Buddhist raft discussions, and Sells on apophatic unsaying. The dissolving portion is also standard in fana, zuowang, and Dzogchen descriptions. The new part is the comparative axis and its predicted consequences, not the individual patterns.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:140:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Sells on apophatic unsaying, or the raft and ladder motifs, this idea proposes a three-way comparative axis and claims that the axis predicts verification and transmission better than doctrine alone."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited communal practice, and radical Other Power cases where the analyst cannot cleanly separate custody, entry, and receiving surface.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If practice and realization are nondual, there may be no discrete landing event and no separate receiving surface. If a person is gradually formed by inherited communal participation before explicit assent, the receiving surface may be socialized rather than locally chosen. If radical Other Power refuses any self-power residue, calling entrusting a human surface may distort the doctrine by reintroducing the agency it rejects."
