reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:65:    "\"Dogen\" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:94:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and problem-solving, not entry into transformative practice after self-negation or vow-held and grace-held beginning.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:97:      "source": "Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:118:      "difference": "Tannisho is a primary case rather than a generalized comparative instrument.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:119:      "novelty_impact": "Very high reduction for Other Power examples and for denial of self-generated threshold entry.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:121:      "source": "Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:147:    "Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, ritual-first entry, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, continuous authorization, radical Other Power, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:148:    "Compare predictive value against Rambo conversion stages, Lofland-Stark conversion conditions, Van Gennep and Turner liminality, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament agency styles, Lave and Wenger legitimate peripheral participation, upaya pedagogy, religious socialization, VCE factor coding, transformative learning theory, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:154:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.54. The four-field compression is useful, but most components have strong near-neighbors in prior Lumenary audits, conversion theory, rites-of-passage theory, doctrine-as-grammar, religious problem-solving styles, legitimate peripheral participation, grace theology, Pure Land Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, VCE factor coding, and Meno-style inquiry paradoxes. The remaining contribution is a conditional first-break rule plus a split-source predictive test, not a discovery-level doctrine candidate.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:157:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is already obvious as conversion stages, initiation, grace, Other Power, self-power, upaya, doctrine-as-grammar, socialization, or apprenticeship. They cannot identify cases where the four fields predict warnings or repairs better than tradition identity, teacher experience, institutional context, or clinical risk.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:160:      "Is this four-field grammar more than familiar conversion theory, grace versus works, self-power versus Other Power, upaya, doctrine-as-grammar, and ordinary lineage pedagogy?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:181:      "Tannisho and Rennyo Ofumi, BDK English Tripitaka, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:186:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, liminality, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, contemplative adverse effects, grace, Other Power, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:187:    "structural_observation": "Orange is a near-exact high-severity case: prayer, will, desire, assent, and the beginning of faith are attributed to grace, not unaided nature. Tannisho supplies a vow-held analogue, where entrusting to Amida's Primal Vow displaces self-power and reshapes warning language. SN 22.59 does not fit the same entry grammar, because it negates ownership of aggregates and moves through disenchantment and release without clearly requiring an external break mechanism. Dogen is the strongest anomaly: practice and realization are treated as one, and beginner practice is already implicated in realization, so entry and fruition cannot be cleanly sequenced as threshold and later attainment."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:196:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Chinul's sudden awakening and gradual cultivation, plus radical Jodo Shinshu Other Power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Chinul makes the same cultivation necessary after awakening but empty of production, so the claimant status changes by stage. Shinran makes even entrusting wholly Other Power, so calling vow, hearing, or trust a support locus may be an analyst's domestication of grace. These cases strain any clean grid that treats support and claimant as stable cells."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:12:    "Right effort, Other Power, direct introduction, and practice-realization differ by which functions are required and which owner is disallowed.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:49:    "Pargament religious coping self-directing deferring collaborative God control",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:51:    "Shinran Other Power self power calculation hakarai entrusting mind",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:54:    "Dogen practice realization one Bendowa gaining idea",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:62:      "overlap": "Very close structural neighbor. Pargament's self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already ask whether responsibility for change rests with the person, God, or both.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:63:      "source": "Kenneth Pargament et al., religious coping styles, summarized in https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/ and https://link.springer.com/rwe/10.1007/978-3-030-24348-7_578"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:73:      "novelty_impact": "High reduction. The forbidden-claimant idea is strongly present in Shinran.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:74:      "overlap": "Near exact for source-centered paths. Shinran already separates entrusting from self-powered calculation and treats the practicer's claim as the problem.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:75:      "source": "Shinran, Other Power and hakarai, https://shinranworks.com/glossary/ and https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:110:    "Read Pargament et al. on religious problem-solving styles directly before claiming novelty.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:112:    "Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, especially SN 45.8, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Chinul, Longchen Rabjam, and Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:116:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.57 to about 0.45. The prohibited-claimant column is useful, but the main structure is strongly anticipated by self-power and other-power, monergism and synergism, Pargament's religious coping styles, locus-of-control research, Sri Vaishnava grace-effort debates, and local capacity-ledger work.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:119:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Teachers say the rubric merely renames standard warnings, or psychologists say it is Pargament and locus-of-control language applied to contemplative texts. Practitioners find claimant language alien or misleading.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:134:      "Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:140:      "Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Other Power, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:143:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The closest structural gap is not self-power versus other-power, which is well known, but the per-function grid of support locus plus prohibited claimant. Still, Pargament's religious coping styles, religious locus of control, Christian monergism and synergism, Sri Vaishnava markata and marjara, Buddhist upaya, Engler's ego-strength thesis, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger work already occupy much of the architecture.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:144:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 makes the practitioner the grammatical agent of desire, persistence, intent, prevention, abandonment, cultivation, and maintenance. Shinran's Letter to Senshin makes settled shinjin incompatible with calculation on the practicer's side, and says no working is true working. This comparison supports the function-claimant split: practice can retain necessary operations while changing who may claim them. But the split is already explicit in the primary materials, especially in Shinran, so the rubric mostly generalizes an old tension rather than discovering it."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.json:156:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, religious locus-of-control work, self-power and other-power debates, monergism and synergism, and the local capacity ledger, this idea says that each required practice function should be coded twice: where the function is operationally supported and which claimant the tradition forbids from owning it."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Bahiya's immediate release, Tannisho's non-practice Other Power, and Dogen's practice-realization collapse the model's tendency to locate direction in analyzable layers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "This lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model remains useful as a coding heuristic only if it includes analyst-frame-refused, no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, and undecidable values.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Bahiya receives a brief instruction and is said to be released immediately, so textual coding cannot show whether direction came from prior training, readiness, teacher authority, or the instruction itself. Tannisho denies self-owned practice calculation and assigns decisive efficacy to Other Power, so calling nembutsu a directed practice can distort the source. Dogen-style practice-realization refuses a clean sequence of practice first and result later, so layer location may be an analyst imposition."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Layer scores should predict held-out warnings and repairs above baselines using tradition name, technique family, teacher style, social ecology, Pargament agency style, Lutz matrix dimensions, and VCE factors.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:30:      "test_surface": "Six-case corpus: MN 10, Vivekachudamani, Tannisho, Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and The Cloud of Unknowing.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:61:    "Pargament religious problem-solving styles self-directing deferring collaborative",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:64:    "Tannisho non-practice non-good Other Power primary text"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:80:      "difference": "It does not foreground teacher authorization, community interpretation, Other Power, or post-insight custody as comparative religion variables.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:116:      "difference": "Pargament studies religious coping and problem-solving, not fine-grained contemplative instruction layers or cross-tradition transfer.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:119:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:138:    "Add mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited practice, practice-realization, radical Other Power, direct recognition, teacher-held, vow-held, grace-held, community-held, no-practice-frame, no-direction-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:140:    "Compare predictive value against Dunne mindfulness styles, Lutz phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck grammar, Pargament agency styles, habitus and hysteresis, situated learning, VCE factors, teacher style, social ecology, intensity, and clinical-risk baselines.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:143:    "Use Bahiya, Tannisho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, direct introduction, and successful dual practice as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:146:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.78 to about 0.42. The useful contribution is not the broad claim that practices carry direction through many layers. That is strongly anticipated by primary texts, Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, situated learning, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The surviving extension is the pre-registered split-source test: code where direction enters, then predict warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:150:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners provide concrete cases where a layer-coded mismatch predicts a repair that a generic technique, tradition, or clinical-risk model misses, for example when a noting-trained student applies deconstructive effort inside direct recognition, or when a Pure Land convert treats nembutsu as self-owned achievement despite instruction to entrust.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:176:      "Tannisho sections I to X, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:179:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become too absorbent if every difference is assigned to some layer after the fact. Tannisho and radical Other Power traditions can reject the analyst's practice-direction frame. Dogen-style practice-realization can collapse means and result. Bahiya-style immediacy strains any developmental layer sequence. Community, doctrine, teacher style, clinical risk, and social belonging may explain many cases without this model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:180:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found strong near-neighbors in Dunne on Buddhist mindfulness styles, Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron on the phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Foucault on technologies of the self, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Bourdieu and Wacquant on habitus and hysteresis, Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lave and Wenger on situated learning, Sharf and Katz on context-shaped experience, and Lindahl and Britton's VCE study. This audit did not read full monographs by Lindbeck, Asad, Hadot, Bourdieu, Katz, or Sharf, did not check Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Japanese, Middle English, or Chinese terms, and did not include practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:181:    "structural_observation": "The primary texts support distribution of direction, but they also reduce novelty. MN 10 does not present bare neutral attention, it gives frames, ardency, hindrance work, aggregate analysis, arising, and disappearance. Vivekachudamani directs the seeker from the start through discrimination, dispassion, teacher relation, and self-knowledge. Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-owned practice into entrusting and Other Power, even calling nembutsu non-practice and non-good from the practicer's side. Longchenpa's Trekcho instruction moves through preliminary deconstruction, teacher introduction, recognition of rigpa, and sustaining without effort or clinging. This close read supports the model's layer claim, but the structures are already visible in the sources themselves."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.json:190:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers, the surviving distinct claim is a split-source predictive rule: code where practice direction enters before reading outcomes, then test whether layer mismatch predicts warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects better than technique, tradition label, social ecology, teacher style, and clinical risk. The general idea that practice has layered direction is not original."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:7:Status: draft
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:26:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/mn/mn.022.than.html
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:27:- Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:75:- Meditation safety researchers familiar with VCE and Cheetah House work
