reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:120:      "source": "Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:142:    "Compare predictive value against Rambo conversion stages, Lofland-Stark conversion conditions, Van Gennep and Turner liminality, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Lave and Wenger legitimate peripheral participation, Kupari and Utriainen ritual-learning data, Pargament agency styles, catechumenate scholarship, monastic formation scholarship, upaya pedagogy, VCE factor coding, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:147:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.76 to about 0.43. The candidate is generative, but most of its structure is already present in local Lumenary records, especially Entry-State Ledger, Threshold Grammar Under Translation Strain, Compound Entry Grammar, Layered Authorization of Beginning, and Operational Remainder Ecology. External near-neighbors further reduce the claim: Rambo covers conversion process, Lave and Wenger cover pre-mastery participation, Kupari and Utriainen apply that to religious newcomers, Lindbeck covers doctrine as grammar, Pargament covers agency distribution, Orange and Shinran give near-exact prescriptive beginning cases, Benedict and OCIA give institutional formation cases. The remaining contribution is a sharper label for prescriptive versus retrospective custody, not a discovery-level idea.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:150:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners and scholars say the frame is ordinary grace theology, Other Power, catechumenate, monastic formation, refuge, initiation, lineage pedagogy, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, conversion studies, or legitimate peripheral participation. They cannot identify repairs predicted by custody grammar beyond institution, teacher experience, community ecology, temperament, or clinical risk.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:175:      "Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, BDK English Tripitaka, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:181:    "structural_observation": "Orange is the strongest prescriptive incapacity case: faith's beginning, desire, assent, prayer, and right choice are assigned to grace rather than unaided natural power. Tannisho and Ofumi give a vow-held analogue: entrusting is given by Amida's working, nenbutsu after settled faith is gratitude rather than self-powered production, and the warning profile targets calculation and self-power. Benedict gives institutional and apprenticeship custody: the novice is delayed, tested, placed under a senior, repeatedly exposed to the Rule, and only then incorporated. SN 55.5 is a partial anomaly: it names association with people of integrity, hearing true Dhamma, appropriate attention, and practice in accordance with Dhamma. That is distributed support, but not necessarily a doctrine forbidding self-generated beginning. The close-read result is that the candidate's structure exists in several sources, but its categories are analyst abstractions over older grace, vow, rule, apprenticeship, and stream-entry grammars."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:190:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's agency styles, Orange, Shinran, Benedict, and OCIA, this candidate's only distinct claim is that beginnings should be coded as custody of unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation, and that entry doctrine should be classified as either retrospective narration or prescriptive control. That difference is useful but thin, because prior Lumenary records and older sources already contain most of the structure."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:25:- Tannisho, BDK translation, especially chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11 and Rennyo postscript, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:28:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-realization sources, for anomaly pressure, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:30:Structural observation: Tannisho strongly supports vow-held custody: Amida's vow carries salvific efficacy and self-power calculation is treated as deviation. Yet it still requires hearing, entrusting, teacher lineage, and restricted readiness, so a receiving surface remains visible. SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the aggregates, but the discourse still depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and seeing with right understanding, so causal-process custody does not eliminate local investigation. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 gives the opposite residue policy: ordinary objectification fails, but the hidden knower or inner controller is authorized as the remainder. Dogen's practice-realization strains the model because practice and realization are not cleanly separable stages, making custody and receiving surface look like an analyst-imposed split. These primary texts support the distinction as a useful coding question, but not as a proven independent structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:32:Secondary literature gap: This audit used accessible translations and open academic or practitioner-facing sources. It did not fully close-read Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen or Mahamudra manuals, John of the Cross, Teresa of Avila, Christian grace controversy sources, or Sanskrit, Pali, Japanese, Tibetan, and Latin originals. It also did not run practitioner interviews. Novelty should not rise without split-source coding and interview evidence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:38:- Pargament religion problem-solving self-directing deferring collaborative coping agency God practitioner
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:39:- Pure Land Other Power shinjin self-power calculation Tannisho entrusting vow
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:47:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one no-threshold practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:52:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion, 1988, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency distribution across person and sacred power. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already code different relationships between individual action and divine control.; difference: Pargament studies religious problem-solving and coping, not self-weakening contemplative paths with separate receiving-surface coding and verification practices.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction. Custody assignment must be baseline-tested against religious coping and locus-of-control models.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:59:- Tannisho and Jodo Shinshu Other Power sources, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Very close for vow-held custody plus entrusting as the human-side interface. Self-power calculation already functions as a named failure mode.; difference: The candidate generalizes the structure across traditions and asks whether entrusting-like surfaces differ from custody itself.; novelty impact: Large reduction for Pure Land examples. Novelty can only be comparative and predictive.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:65:Unlike Pargament's agency styles, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, VCE adverse-effects research, upaya capacity pedagogy, Pure Land Other Power, Christian attention and grace theology, pointing-out instruction, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that the assigned holder of transformation and the practitioner's required mode of availability should be coded separately, then tested to see whether the second variable predicts warnings, sequencing, teacher repairs, and verification beyond the first.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:69:Candidate: Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited communal practice, and radical Other Power cases where the analyst cannot cleanly separate custody, entry, and receiving surface.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:71:Why it strains the model: If practice and realization are nondual, there may be no discrete landing event and no separate receiving surface. If a person is gradually formed by inherited communal participation before explicit assent, the receiving surface may be socialized rather than locally chosen. If radical Other Power refuses any self-power residue, calling entrusting a human surface may distort the doctrine by reintroducing the agency it rejects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:85:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:97:- Does this model predict any sequencing or safeguard you would not already derive from upaya, grace theology, Other Power teaching, spiritual direction, teacher experience, or adverse-effects research?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:120:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.77 to about 0.55. The idea is useful and testable, but most components are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary ledgers, Pargament's religious coping styles, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, VCE and teacher-factor research, upaya capacity pedagogy, Pure Land Other Power, Christian attention and grace theology, and pointing-out models. The remaining contribution is the explicit separability test between custody assignment and receiving surface.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:130:- Compare predictive value against Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck grammar, Asad discursive tradition, VCE variables, upaya capacity pedagogy, grace theology, Other Power scholarship, pointing-out instruction literature, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:27:- Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, translation by Taitetsu Unno, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:29:Structural observation: SN 45.8 parses the path through practitioner-cultivated functions: right view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The grammar permits the practitioner to perform decisive training functions, though under Buddhist doctrinal constraints. Tannisho shifts decisive efficacy away from self-power and toward entrusting, Other Power, and the Primal Vow, while also warning against claiming disciples or treating nembutsu as self-owned practice or merit. This supports the candidate's entry-claimant link. It also shows the main risk: the same Shinran material supplies entry grammar, claimant prohibition, danger, and verification language at once, so a prediction test can easily become circular.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:33:Risk of overread: High. The phrase grammar risks renaming Lindbeck, Rambo, Pargament, Berger, religious socialization theory, and Lumenary's own Entry-State Ledger unless the candidate produces non-circular coding fields and predictive wins. It also risks imposing analyst-owned agency language on traditions that explicitly refuse the claimant frame.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:40:- Pargament religion problem solving three styles self directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:41:- Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power nembutsu not practice good act
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:43:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization are one translation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:52:- Kenneth Pargament et al. religious problem-solving styles, summarized in Watson and Chen, Religious Problem Solving Styles within an American Religious Ideological Surround, https://hc.edu/gideon/wp-content/uploads/sites/79/2023/02/Religious-Problem-Solving-Styles-within-an-American-Religious-Ideological-Surround.pdf: overlap: Close for distributing agency between person and God through self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles.; difference: The candidate applies agency distribution to entry into transformative paths and includes teacher, community, ritual, vow, text, lineage, family formation, and verification rules, not only coping with problems.; novelty impact: High reduction for agency distribution. Moderate extension if the rubric predicts entry failure and repair beyond coping styles.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:58:- Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/: overlap: Very close for load relocation and forbidden claimant. Shinran's Other Power grammar denies self-power as the decisive basis of liberation and relocates decisive function to the Vow and Name.; difference: Shinran gives a specific Pure Land case, while the candidate proposes a cross-tradition entry and claimant grammar with prediction tests.; novelty impact: High reduction and high anomaly pressure. The candidate may mostly generalize Shinran and grace patterns into coding language.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:65:Unlike Rambo's conversion-process model, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar model, Pargament's religious agency styles, Berger's plausibility structures, upaya pedagogy, liminality theory, Shinran's Other Power grammar, Orange grace theology, religious socialization theory, and Lumenary's Entry-State Ledger, this idea claims that entry mechanism and forbidden claimant form one testable agency grammar, and that a split-source independence audit can determine whether that grammar predicts safeguards and verification practices without circularly reusing the same text as both cause and evidence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:77:- If: Entry doctrine and claimant prohibition are separable variables in at least some traditions. Then: Blind coders using only entry texts can distinguish entry mechanism from forbidden claimant, and those separate codes predict different warning and verification patterns in later manuals with above-chance agreement. Weakens if: Coders cannot separate entry mechanism from claimant rule, or later safeguards can be predicted equally well from generic tradition labels, conversion-stage theory, religious socialization, or Pargament agency styles. Test surface: Split-source manual coding across Shinran Pure Land, Theravada path-factor texts, Orange or Augustinian grace texts, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:78:- If: Strong anti-self-claimant traditions should generate distinctive safeguards against moral license, despair, counterfeit passivity, or self-power contamination. Then: Texts and teachers in Other Power, grace, and surrender-centered traditions repeatedly warn against predictable misuse of non-self-efficacy language, and these warnings differ from effort-centered path warnings. Weakens if: Warnings are not distinctive, are mostly generic moral warnings, or are better predicted by institutional history, teacher style, sectarian polemic, or social setting than by claimant grammar. Test surface: Primary manuals, sermons, letters, and practitioner interviews in Jodo Shinshu, Christian grace traditions, bhakti or prapatti, and Sufi tawakkul.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:85:- Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.72 to about 0.58. The idea is not a discovery-level concept. Its entry ecology is strongly anticipated by Rambo, Berger, liminality, situated learning, and religious socialization. Its grammar language is anticipated by Lindbeck. Its agency distribution is anticipated by Pargament and grace or Other Power sources. Its support-locus and safeguard rubric is very close to prior Lumenary Entry-State Ledger, Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant, and Credit Distribution records. The remaining contribution is an extension: an independence audit that tries to prevent construct leakage between entry doctrine, claimant rule, anthropology, safeguard, and verification.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:129:- Run a comparison against baseline models: Rambo conversion stages, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, upaya capacity pedagogy, liminality, situated learning, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity ledger.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:12:Before asking what a practice does with authority over its result, ask whether it claims to produce a separable result at all. Custody, release, and correction vocabulary applies only to instrumental practices. Dogen's practice-realization and Shinran's Other Power dissolve the tool frame because sitting or entrusting is not owned as a means to a later product.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:19:- Shinran's Other Power denies practicer calculation and owned efficacy.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:26:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:27:- Dogen shusho itto and Shinran jinen honi, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 is explicitly instrumental: effort with the raft gets one across, then the raft should not be carried. Dogen's shusho itto demolishes the cause-effect separation between practice and realization, while Shinran's jinen honi removes calculation by the practicer and locates efficacy in Other Power. The contrast supports a scope distinction, but not a discovery: the instrumental versus non-instrumental contrast is already structurally visible in the primary texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit did not read Eihei Shingi, full Bendowa or Genjokoan in Japanese, Shinran's Japanese around jinen and hakarai, Tannisho anti-license passages in Japanese, ritual theory in depth, Aristotle praxis and poiesis sources, or empirical studies of autotelic practice and perfectionism. These are necessary before raising novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:33:Risk of overread: High. Non-instrumental self-description does not mean absence of discipline, correction, warnings, institutional form, or effects. Dogen still requires continuous practice, and Shinran still has nembutsu, entrusting, and cautions. The model may confuse no owned result with no practical structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:38:- Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power practicer
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:39:- Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act Other Power self power
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:40:- MN 22 raft simile instrumental practice crossing let go
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:45:- Pargament religious problem solving styles agency God control
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:49:- Internal Lumenary audit, When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json: overlap: Extremely close. The prior audit already says keep, release, embody assumes practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and that Shinran and Dogen break those assumptions.; difference: This candidate uses the broader word instrumentality and asks whether the practice claims to produce a separable result.; novelty impact: Major internal downgrade. The scope-gate framing is useful but not a new discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:52:- Shinran, On Jinen Honi, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/: overlap: Very close. Shinran explicitly rejects practicer calculation and describes Other Power as no working, which undermines self-owned method efficacy.; difference: The candidate uses Shinran as a non-tool boundary case rather than as Pure Land doctrine alone.; novelty impact: Downgrades the non-ownership claim to known primary-text structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:55:- Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency distribution between individual and divine action, especially deferring and collaborative styles.; difference: Pargament studies coping and control attribution, not whether a practice produces a separable result.; novelty impact: For Shinran-style agency relocation, novelty is low unless the separable-result gate predicts warnings beyond agency-style variables.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:59:Unlike Dogen's practice-realization, Shinran's Other Power, autotelic activity theory, non-instrumental ritual theory, MacIntyre's internal goods, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits, this idea's possible contribution is a practical scope gate for comparative coding: ask first whether a practice claims to produce a separable result before applying custody, release, or correction vocabulary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:65:Why it strains the model: If Eihei Shingi, Soto training, Shinran's cautions against licensed evil, nembutsu practice, and community transmission all function as retained disciplines with real effects, then non-instrumentality is not outside the custody apparatus. It is a different custody location: form-held, vow-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, or community-held.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:71:- If: The separable-result question is a real scope gate. Then: Texts and manuals coded as non-instrumental from doctrinal passages will show less result-custody language and more conduct, form, vow, teacher, or community correction language in held-out sources. Weakens if: Self-described non-instrumental traditions contain result-custody language as centrally as instrumental traditions, or coders cannot distinguish result refusal from result relocation. Test surface: Split-source coding of Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, koan curricula, Advaita inquiry, apophatic Christian sources, Sufi fana and baqa, and ritual manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:80:- Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:93:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners and scholars say this is already standard as practice-realization, Other Power, autotelic ritual, internal goods, non-attachment, grace, or non-gaining mind, and that the scope gate adds no predictive guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.34. The instrumental versus non-instrumental distinction is old and appears directly in Dogen, Shinran, ritual theory, autotelic activity theory, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits. The useful extension is narrower: using separable-result as a pre-coding scope gate for Lumenary's custody and release apparatus. Human-condition fit is strong for functioning perfectionists, founders, students, creators, and professionals who convert every activity into proof of worth. It is not for under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, severe depression, dissociation, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, coercive workloads, or people who need concrete completed outcomes restored before resultless practice is safe.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md:120:- Read non-instrumental ritual theory, autotelic flow literature, MacIntyre on practices, Dogen's Eihei Shingi, Bendowa and Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho in stronger translations before public use.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:7:Status: draft
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:21:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If nembutsu, zazen, teacher correction, vows, forms, and ordinary conduct function as retained or embodied methods, then the custody model is not abolished. It is relocated from self-ownership to vow, practice, teacher, community, or form. The boundary claim would then be overstated."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:12:    "Shinran's Other Power refuses practitioner ownership, calculation, and self-generated entrusting.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:25:  "exact_claim": "The keep, release, embody model silently assumes that the practitioner provisionally owns the method and that there is an after in which custody of the result can be decided. Radical Other Power and practice-realization break those assumptions: in Shinran's jinen honi the practitioner never owns the method, trust, or result, while in Dogen's shusho-itto there is no discrete after outside practice. Therefore the custody model is bounded, and for depleted over-managing people the prompt to decide what to keep, release, or embody can become one more burden.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot separate refusal from relocation, or retain, release, embody categories work equally well across Shinran, Dogen, Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, apophatic Christian, and Sufi sources."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:50:    "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power natural working of the primal vow",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:51:    "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act practicer Other Power self power",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:52:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto verification outside practice",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:55:    "Pargament deferring religious coping style agency God control",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:63:      "overlap": "Extremely close. Both argue that release teaching applies to active-voice result-ownership, while Other Power, practice-realization, and no-attainment sources strain or refuse the release frame.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:67:      "difference": "The candidate uses Shinran as a scope condition for a comparative after-use model and as a modern caution for over-management.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:69:      "overlap": "Very close for the non-ownership claim: natural working and Other Power oppose practicer calculation and self-generated control.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:70:      "source": "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:75:      "overlap": "Very close for denying nembutsu as the practitioner's self-powered good act or possessed practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:76:      "source": "Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:85:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping style and control attribution, not method-completion temporality or practitioner ownership as scope conditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:88:      "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:101:    "Close-read Shinran's Japanese terms around jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen on shusho-itto and non-gaining, and practitioner manuals where concrete guidance appears.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:104:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.28. The non-ownership and no-after structures are well established in Shinran and Dogen, and the core Lumenary comparison is already present in the recent audit of You cannot release what you never held. The modern caution overlaps with known rumination, perfectionism, and burnout risks. Human-condition fit is strong for depleted over-managers, caregivers, founders, professionals, students, and serious practitioners who turn even rest into performance. It is not for people who need planning, accountability, medication, therapy, social support, or material workload reduction, nor for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, or responsibility avoidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:107:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as Other Power, practice-realization, grace, surrender, non-calculation, or non-gaining mind, and that the no-audit prompt is simply rest from rumination or basic clinical caution.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:119:      "Theravada teachers familiar with raft and non-clinging instructions",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:127:      "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:128:      "Dogen, Bendowa and shusho-itto practice-realization sources, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:130:    "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The claim may exaggerate refusal into absence. Other Power and practice-realization may not abolish all custody questions; they may relocate custody to vow, teacher, text, sangha, conduct, or practice itself. The human-condition claim may also overgeneralize depletion, since some burned-out people need structure and accountability rather than non-audit.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:131:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese sources, Dogen commentarial scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Pargament's full agency-style work, or ethnographic practitioner accounts. It also did not verify whether other traditions with inherited practice, ritual-first formation, or apophatic unsaying similarly refuse the ownership-and-after assumptions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:132:    "structural_observation": "Shinran relocates efficacy to Other Power and warns against calculation, so the practitioner is not the owner who later decides how to carry the method. Dogen's practice-realization collapses the gap between practice and verification, so a later custody decision is not the native shape of the path. These are strong boundary cases against a universal after-use grid, but they do not eliminate all guidance: Shin still has nembutsu, warnings, and entrusting language, and Soto still has zazen, discipline, teacher correction, and conduct."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:144:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, Pargament's agency styles, burnout rumination literature, and prior Lumenary release and custody models, this idea's possible contribution is an explicit scope test: before applying keep, release, or embody guidance, first ask whether the tradition grants provisional practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and whether the person has enough agency to benefit from a custody prompt."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:28:- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:31:Structural observation: SN 22.89 already separates a formal path achievement from a remaining gradient: the noble disciple has abandoned lower fetters and does not assume 'I am this,' yet residual 'I am' conceit, desire, and obsession remain until further contemplation uproots them. SN 45.8 gives a clear practitioner-agency grammar for right effort. Tannisho gives the opposite formal marker: entrusting, non-calculation, and Amida's working, while warning against claiming nembutsu as one's own practice. Cross-reading these texts supports the candidate's two-track architecture, but also shows that much of the architecture is already available in primary sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:33:Secondary literature gap: The audit found strong near-neighbors but did not fully close-read Steve Bein, Taitetsu Unno, Pargament, Lindbeck, Trungpa, VCE coding materials, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Rennyo letters, or Tibetan manuals beyond the cited Longchen Rabjam text. It also did not check Pali, Japanese, or Tibetan terms directly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:35:Risk of overread: High. The claimant-layer vocabulary is strongly shaped by Theravada categories and may distort Shinran, Dzogchen, Soto Zen, and traditions that reject agency accounting. The warning-cluster prediction also risks circular coding unless safeguards are coded from a separate corpus.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:41:- Tannisho Shinran entrusting mind Amida's working not self power primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:44:- Pargament religion problem solving process three styles coping self directing deferring collaborative
