reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:104:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.28. The core is already present in the supplied Who Holds The Gate audit and has close external neighbors in Ignatian direction, spiritual direction, Pargament agency styles, contemplative adverse-effects support, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and self-focused-attention research. Human-condition fit is real but bounded: it serves stable high-achievement practitioners, founders, students, creators, caregivers, and self-directed meditators who convert insight into worth evidence. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive authority settings, or people whose main need is restored self-trust.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:130:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Heart Sutra, Shinran On Jinen-Honi, and Dogen Bendowa or practice-realization sources, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:133:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Still needs full reading of Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, AA sponsorship sources, ERP and scrupulosity treatment literature, VCE person-centered support, spiritual bypassing literature, and achievement-contingent self-worth studies before practice publication.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:134:    "structural_observation": "Ignatius is the closest primary-text neighbor. The director adapts exercises to the exercitant, receives reports of movements and thoughts, reveals dangerous secrecy to a confessor or spiritual person, and is also restrained from seizing the exercitant's final choice. The scruple notes already distinguish useful sensitivity from harmful over-fineness and counsel a mean. MN 22 adds that the raft must be grasped correctly before release, so release is not a generic self-check. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on Prajnaparamita. Shinran and Dogen strain the whole model because no-calculation and practice-realization refuse a clean separable product that the practitioner can audit."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:146:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian direction, Pargament agency styles, VCE support mapping, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and the prior Lumenary Who Holds The Gate record, this candidate says that a post-practice check must first ask who should hold the diagnostic today, because the same check can repair bypassing and worsen achievement-contingent self-scoring. That distinction is useful, but it is mostly a renamed and narrower safety-routing heuristic."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:12:A practice-routing model must decide three things before recommending a return test: whether the practice permits result language, whether the practitioner is presently bypassing or self-scoring, and who should hold the diagnostic gate. Self-administered return attention may help the bypasser who uses insight to avoid conduct. For the compulsive scorer, the gate should be externally held by a teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or replaced by resultless practice. For oscillators, the assignment must be state-level and revisable, not a stable identity label.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:17:- The model distinguishes a bypassing state from a compulsive self-scoring state.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:28:- Shinran, On Jinen Honi, and Dogen shusho itto summary, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/ and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:30:Structural observation: Ignatius already makes gate custody explicit. The exercitant reports movements and thoughts, the director adapts exercises, and disclosure to a confessor or spiritual person breaks the secrecy of deceptive movements. Yet Annotation 15 also limits the director, the guide is not supposed to seize the final choice. Shinran strains the model from the opposite side: jinen honi rejects practicer calculation and warns that even talking about no-working can become another form of working. Dogen also strains the return-test frame because practice and realization are not separated as cause and later product. The candidate's structure is therefore not a discovery at the primary-text level. Its possible contribution is a routing rule for deciding when Ignatian-style disclosure, clinical support, fixed-rule gating, or no-result practice is appropriate.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit did not read full Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, full Dogen Bendowa or Eihei Shingi, Shinran and Tannisho in Japanese, OCD scrupulosity treatment literature beyond abstracts, or the full measurement-based care and guided self-help literatures. It also needs direct work in perfectionism, achievement-contingent self-worth, and contemplative adverse effects before public practice guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:39:- Dogen shusho itto practice realization result cause effect Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:40:- Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power practicer working
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:41:- Pargament religion problem solving process self-directing deferring collaborative coping
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:44:- spiritual bypassing Picciotto Fox Neto phenomenology psychological avoidance spiritualizing
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:56:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion 1988, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency and responsibility distribution. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already model who is experienced as holding problem-solving responsibility.; difference: Pargament concerns coping with God and individual agency, not diagnostic gate custody across teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no practice.; novelty impact: Reduces novelty for support-locus language but leaves room for a practice-safety routing extension.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:57:- Cuijpers et al., Effectiveness and Acceptability of Cognitive Behavior Therapy Delivery Formats in Adults With Depression, JAMA Psychiatry 2019, https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapsychiatry/fullarticle/2730724: overlap: Close clinical analog. Guided self-help and unguided self-help differ by human support, and treatment format affects effectiveness and acceptability.; difference: The source does not address spiritual return tests, result-language scope, or bypassing versus self-scoring states.; novelty impact: Downgrades the claim that support-holder assignment is new. The candidate should compare itself against guided, unguided, and stepped-care baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:60:- Spiritual bypassing literature, for example Picciotto, Fox, and Neto, A phenomenology of spiritual bypass, Journal of Spirituality in Mental Health 2018, indexed at https://openurl.ebsco.com/fulltext/gcd%3A132497915, and Fox and Picciotto, https://brill.com/view/journals/cvj/64/2/article-p227_7.xml: overlap: Close for the bypasser category: spiritual ideas or practices can defend against difficult emotion, psychological work, responsibility, and ordinary conduct.; difference: The literature does not combine bypass detection with non-instrumental scope gating and gate-custody assignment.; novelty impact: Downgrades the bypasser half of the model to known clinical-spiritual territory.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:65:Unlike Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE person-centered support, Pargament agency styles, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, spiritual bypassing literature, and prior Lumenary return and scope-gate models, this claim says a public practice instruction should pass through three ordered gates: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and custody of the diagnostic itself. Its novelty depends on whether that three-gate routing predicts harm, repair, or non-fit better than existing spiritual direction, clinical triage, and contemplative-safety frameworks.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:77:- If: Result-language permission is a real first gate rather than an analyst's imposed vocabulary. Then: Split-source coding will show that texts coded as instrumental from doctrinal or instruction passages contain more held-out return, fruit, stewardship, or conduct-test warnings, while Dogen and Shinran-style non-instrumental cases contain more form, vow, no-calculation, or practice-realization correction language. Weakens if: Coders cannot reliably distinguish instrumental from non-instrumental cases, or held-out warning and correction language does not differ after controlling for tradition, teacher style, and institution. Test surface: Blind coding of Ignatius, MN 22, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho, Rinzai koan training, apophatic Christian texts, Sufi fana and baqa sources, and modern practice manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:79:- If: Oscillation is state-level and revisable, not a trait label. Then: Within-person diary or EMA data will show the same practitioner moving between bypassing and scoring states across contexts, and state-level routing will predict next-day outcomes better than a one-time trait classification. Weakens if: Trait labels predict outcomes as well as state-level data, or people classified as oscillators do not show meaningful within-person switching. Test surface: Two-week ecological momentary assessment with brief prompts after practice, work review, conflict, and rest periods.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.42. The gate-holder idea is already close to Ignatian discernment, spiritual direction, contemplative adverse-effects support, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, Pargament agency styles, and OCD reassurance literature. The surviving contribution is narrower: a Lumenary safety-routing heuristic that combines result-language permission, current bypassing or scoring state, and diagnostic custody. Human-condition fit is real but bounded. It is for functioning high achievers, founders, students, creators, professionals, and spiritual practitioners who either use insight to avoid conduct or convert practice into proof of worth. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, coercive workloads, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive communities, or people without trustworthy support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:130:- Read full sources before public use: Ignatian directorial literature, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, Pargament, measurement-based care, guided self-help, rumination and self-focused attention, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and scrupulosity ERP.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:28:- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:30:Structural observation: SN 22.59 negates ownership of all aggregates and moves through disenchantment, dispassion, and release, so continuity is carried by instruction, discernment, and practice process rather than an authorized self. Chandogya repeatedly authorizes an underlying Self, but 6.14 also uses a teacher and stepwise inquiry as the way a blindfolded person finds the way home. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 relocates continuity into an unseen inner controller. Tannisho relocates decisive support into Amida's vow, true entrusting, teacher lineage, and non-calculating nembutsu, while refusing ownership of disciples or practice. This close read strongly supports the candidate's comparative frame, but also shows that much of the structure is already explicit in primary texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully read Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Mahmood's Politics of Piety, Bourdieu, Rambo, Lave and Wenger, Shinran's full Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, or Tibetan manuals beyond Longchen Rabjam. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Tibetan terms were not checked directly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:45:- religious coping self directing deferring collaborative Pargament agency
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:49:- Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power calculation primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:50:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:59:- Pargament religious coping styles and Brief RCOPE, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/2/1/51: overlap: Close for distributing control across self, God, and collaborative self-God relations, and for treating religious coping as multimodal and dynamic.; difference: Pargament is about coping and control, not self-negating soteriology or authorized residue after negation.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the support-locus axis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:62:- Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa, and Longchen Rabjam Trekcho primary materials, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/; https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction: overlap: Very close primary evidence for theologically relocated support, no-boundary practice-realization, guru reliance, vows, solitude, and post-recognition training.; difference: The candidate names these as variables in one cross-tradition model.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Several allegedly new variables are already visible in the source texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:67:Unlike extended mind religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, VCE, Pargament, Buddhist continuity-without-self literature, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating paths preserve transformability through a codable continuity ecology and predicts that dissolution target plus residue policy will partly forecast where continuity is stored after institutional, ritual, and historical controls.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:73:Why it strains the model: Dogen's Bendowa denies a clean boundary in realization and denies a beginning in practice. Inherited religious participation can also preserve continuity before any explicit self-negating doctrine is consciously adopted. In both cases, the model may impose a migration story where the tradition presents no transfer, no threshold, or no separate continuity problem.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:81:- If: Practice ecology can precede doctrine but should leave historical traces when it does. Then: Where support structures predate doctrinal refinement, later doctrine explicitly explains, legitimates, or polices already existing teacher, ritual, vow, or institutional arrangements. Weakens if: Historical cases show no relation between prior ecology and later doctrine, or show doctrine changing without support-ecology change and without new warning or verification patterns. Test surface: Historical comparison of Shinran communities, Soto monastic practice, Theravada reform movements, modern mindfulness programs, and Christian grace controversies.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:90:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:100:- Does the rubric predict warnings or repairs you would not already derive from ordinary pedagogy, spiritual materialism, upaya, coping styles, or trauma-informed care?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:103:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is standard no-self continuity, Other Power, practice-realization, guru-yoga, grace, upaya, spiritual materialism, or ordinary pastoral sequencing. They cannot identify new predictions, repairs, or failure clusters.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:123:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.80 to about 0.56. The candidate is useful and testable, but the core components are already strongly anticipated by extended and socially extended religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's grammar model, Pargament's agency styles, VCE influencing-factor coding, Buddhist continuity-without-self debates, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The remaining contribution is a consolidated comparative coding hypothesis with explicit causal-priority tests.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:131:- Compare predictive power against extended mind, Asad, Lindbeck, Pargament, VCE, upaya, conversion studies, situated learning, socialization, habitus, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:7:Status: draft
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:19:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power as a lens by subtracting the assumption that every needed function must be owned by the practitioner. The method's distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against SN 45.8 on right effort.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:20:- Primary close-reading: SN 45.8 Magga-Vibhanga Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN45_8.html, against Shinran's Letter to Senshin. SN 45.8 authorizes generated desire, persistence, intent, prevention, abandonment, cultivation, and maintenance. Shinran forbids calculation on the practicer's side. The comparison reveals that function and claimant must be separated.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:22:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:30:The strongest counterexample is Chinul's sudden awakening and gradual cultivation. In Secrets on Cultivating the Mind, awakening is sudden, later cultivation is necessary, and true cultivation eliminates without treating anything as truly eliminated. The same action can be authorized or forbidden depending on whether it relies on awakening or on goal-seeking delusion. That may make the rubric too stage-dependent to remain clean. Radical Jodo Shinshu adds a sharper theological objection: if true entrusting is Amida's working, even calling the vow a support locus may still be an outside analyst's way of domesticating grace. The Shinran lens also biases the analysis toward ownership suspicion; right effort corrects this by showing that desire, effort, and maintenance can be medicines rather than theft. The model should be weakened if primary manuals do not show recurring wrong-claimant warnings, or if practitioners say ownership language is alien to their actual training.
