reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:172:      "Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:175:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The claimant-layer vocabulary is strongly shaped by Theravada categories and may distort Shinran, Dzogchen, Soto Zen, and traditions that reject agency accounting. The warning-cluster prediction also risks circular coding unless safeguards are coded from a separate corpus.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:176:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit found strong near-neighbors but did not fully close-read Steve Bein, Taitetsu Unno, Pargament, Lindbeck, Trungpa, VCE coding materials, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Rennyo letters, or Tibetan manuals beyond the cited Longchen Rabjam text. It also did not check Pali, Japanese, or Tibetan terms directly.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:177:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.89 already separates a formal path achievement from a remaining gradient: the noble disciple has abandoned lower fetters and does not assume 'I am this,' yet residual 'I am' conceit, desire, and obsession remain until further contemplation uproots them. SN 45.8 gives a clear practitioner-agency grammar for right effort. Tannisho gives the opposite formal marker: entrusting, non-calculation, and Amida's working, while warning against claiming nembutsu as one's own practice. Cross-reading these texts supports the candidate's two-track architecture, but also shows that much of the architecture is already available in primary sources."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:186:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Khemaka, Shinran, Dzogchen instructions, Dogen, Pargament, Bein, Trungpa, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the comparative unit is a two-track transfer profile and predicts that safeguards cluster where formal agency grammar changes while partial dissolution leaves layer-specific reappropriation risks."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:21:    "prediction": "Teams with high start rates and low completion rates will reduce duplicate tickets, abandoned drafts, and rework when action-state gates are enforced before new creation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:144:      "MN 22 raft simile, Heart Sutra no attainment, and Dogen practice-realization, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:148:    "structural_observation": "Zhuangzi and MN 22 both support release of a tool after its work is done, but they presuppose a real catch or crossing. MN 22 also stresses proper grasp before release, which prevents premature quitting. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, so no-attainment is not simple inactivity. Dogen strains the model most, because practice and realization are inseparable, which blocks a universal before-and-after completion rule. These primary texts support a scoped after-use discipline, not the broad claim that finishing is always the next virtue."
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:7:Status: draft
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Radical Jodo Shinshu, especially Tannisho chapters 8 and 10, where nembutsu is not the practitioner's practice or good act and no working is true working.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:40:      "if_model_is_right": "The handoff rubric should add predictive value beyond Pargament-style responsibility allocation and the local capacity ledger.",
