reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:59:    "Buddhist raft parable abandon teachings MN 22 upaya",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:68:      "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles, summarized at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/ and https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:74:      "source": "Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-Dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:77:      "difference": "Tannisho is a primary instance, not a comparative rubric. It may actually break the model by refusing the idea that a human function is first trained and then handed off.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:79:      "overlap": "Near exact for forbidden claimant language. The nembutsu is said to arise from Other Power, and even disciple ownership is rejected.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:80:      "source": "Shinran, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:95:      "difference": "The raft model is about non-clinging to the Dhamma after crossing, not a full transfer ledger of capacities, support holders, and repair practices.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:98:      "source": "MN 22, Alagadd\u016bpama Sutta, raft parable, https://suttacentral.net/mn22/en/bodhi"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:116:    "Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa or Dogen practice-realization sources, and one Christian grace manual.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:121:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.53 to about 0.44. The rubric is generative, but its parts are heavily anticipated by religious coping styles, self-power and other-power discourse, Dogen, Dzogchen manuals, the raft and upaya pattern, Engler, and local Lumenary priors. Treat as a consolidation unless inter-rater coding shows new predictive value.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:145:      "Shinran, Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:148:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found close prior structures in religious coping styles, self-power and other-power, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Engler on ego strength before no-self, the Buddhist raft and upaya pattern, and local Lumenary capacity-ledger and credit-distribution work. I did not find the exact field list as a cross-tradition coding sheet, but the core agency-allocation and means-end reversal are well established.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:149:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 makes right effort operational and practitioner-facing: desire, endeavor, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities are all assigned to the monk's practice field. Tannisho reverses the claimant grammar: nembutsu is not a practice or good act when it arises from Other Power, and claims such as my disciples are rejected because the working belongs to Amida. The comparison supports a real difference in claimant policy, but Tannisho is not a late handoff after training. It often refuses self-claim from the entrance, so the model needs a no-transfer or analyst-frame-refused value."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:161:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, self-power and other-power debates, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary credit models, this idea says the decisive unit is a timed transfer for each required function, with observable safeguards and repairs at that transfer point."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:27:- Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:29:Structural observation: MMK 8 attacks any independently established agent-action structure. Bendowa collapses a simple before-after relation between practice and realization, while still insisting on concrete sitting, teacher transmission, and trust. Together they support the candidate's warning that prohibition language can distort dissolutive traditions. They also reduce novelty, because the anti-appropriation move is primary-textual rather than newly discovered. The possible contribution is the comparative coding rule: do not use forbidden claimant until the tradition's claimability grammar has been identified.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Search reached Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lindbeck on doctrine as rule or grammar, Dogen practice-realization sources, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Chinul sudden awakening and gradual cultivation, Srivaishnava prapatti debates, Gita action-doership passages, Shinran Other Power, and upaya literature. It did not fully close-read Lindbeck's full book, Pargament's full 1988 article, Tibetan commentarial material on direct introduction, Sanskrit Advaita sources on praptasya prapti, or Srivaishnava primary polemics. This blocks candidate-discovery status.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:37:- Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:40:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:46:- spiritual bypassing nondual premature realization claims
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:51:- Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for distributing agency between human actor and God through self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles.; difference: The candidate adds traditions that refuse the agency frame itself and separates claimability stance from credit distribution.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction for regulatory traditions. Less reduction for dissolutive and ontological cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:53:- Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/: overlap: Very close for practice-realization identity and resistance to treating realization as a later object possessed by a practitioner.; difference: The candidate codes this as dissolutive claimability and predicts formalism or attainment-reification failure modes.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The Dogen structure is known; the failure-mode prediction needs testing.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:63:Unlike Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's religious agency styles, Nagarjuna's agent-action critique, Dogen's practice-realization, Dzogchen primordial purity, Advaita praptasya prapti, Srivaishnava effort-grace debates, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary credit-distribution records, this idea says the first coding question is whether the claiming framework itself is authorized, dissolved, ontologically denied, or stage-dependent. Its possible contribution is not the anti-appropriation insight, but the rule that support-locus and forbidden-claimant rubrics are valid only after that prior stance is coded.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:77:- If: Ontological denial produces a distinctive premature-realization failure mode. Then: Advaita and Dzogchen teachers should report recurring cases where students use already-present language to avoid preparation, conduct, integration, or verification. Weakens if: These cases are no more common than in regulatory traditions, or spiritual bypassing explains them without reference to ontological claimability. Test surface: Practitioner interviews, adverse-practice reports, and comparison with spiritual-bypassing literature.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:87:- Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:91:- Contemplative clinicians familiar with spiritual bypassing and adverse meditation effects
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:100:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is ordinary doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, upaya, grace-effort theology, nondual pedagogy, spiritual bypassing, or prior Lumenary ledger language. Dissolutive and ontological teachers reject the rubric as reifying. Teachers cannot produce stance-specific repairs beyond familiar cautions against pride, laziness, premature claims, or poor integration.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:110:Prediction: Therapies with similar techniques but different agency-frame stance should produce different failure modes. Agency-strengthening models should risk self-blame, surrender-based models should risk passivity, self-dissolving models should risk dissociation or avoidance, and already-whole models should risk bypassing concrete behavioral repair.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:120:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.60. The idea is not a discovery of anti-appropriation, non-doership, practice-realization, already-attained realization, grace-effort distribution, or stage-dependent cultivation. Those are well anticipated by primary texts, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary records. The remaining contribution is a novel synthesis: claimability stance as a prior validity check for support-locus and forbidden-claimant coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:129:- Compare predictive power against Lindbeck grammar, Pargament agency styles, upaya pedagogy, grace-effort theology, spiritual bypassing literature, prior Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, and Entry-Claimant Grammar.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:130:- Use Longchenpa Trekcho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, Pure Land Other Power, Srivaishnava prapatti, and successful cross-training as anomaly tests rather than confirming examples.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:27:- Tannisho sections I to X, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts support distribution of direction, but they also reduce novelty. MN 10 does not present bare neutral attention, it gives frames, ardency, hindrance work, aggregate analysis, arising, and disappearance. Vivekachudamani directs the seeker from the start through discrimination, dispassion, teacher relation, and self-knowledge. Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-owned practice into entrusting and Other Power, even calling nembutsu non-practice and non-good from the practicer's side. Longchenpa's Trekcho instruction moves through preliminary deconstruction, teacher introduction, recognition of rigpa, and sustaining without effort or clinging. This close read supports the model's layer claim, but the structures are already visible in the sources themselves.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The search found strong near-neighbors in Dunne on Buddhist mindfulness styles, Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron on the phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Foucault on technologies of the self, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Bourdieu and Wacquant on habitus and hysteresis, Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lave and Wenger on situated learning, Sharf and Katz on context-shaped experience, and Lindahl and Britton's VCE study. This audit did not read full monographs by Lindbeck, Asad, Hadot, Bourdieu, Katz, or Sharf, did not check Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Japanese, Middle English, or Chinese terms, and did not include practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become too absorbent if every difference is assigned to some layer after the fact. Tannisho and radical Other Power traditions can reject the analyst's practice-direction frame. Dogen-style practice-realization can collapse means and result. Bahiya-style immediacy strains any developmental layer sequence. Community, doctrine, teacher style, clinical risk, and social belonging may explain many cases without this model.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:44:- Pargament religious problem-solving styles self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:47:- Tannisho non-practice non-good Other Power primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:53:- Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron, Investigating the Phenomenological Matrix of Mindfulness-Related Practices, https://www.johnddunne.net/uploads/9/8/5/6/9856107/lutzjhadunne___saron_investigating_the_phenomenological_matrix_of_mindfulness-related_practices_from_a_neurocognitive_perspective_american_psychologist_oct_2015_.pdf: overlap: Very close. The phenomenological matrix decomposes mindfulness practices into manipulable dimensions and explicitly includes posture, affective tone, axiological concerns, and practice instructions.; difference: It does not foreground teacher authorization, community interpretation, Other Power, or post-insight custody as comparative religion variables.; novelty impact: High reduction. Any empirical test must show predictive lift beyond this matrix.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:59:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Moderate to close. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already code where agency and divine support are located.; difference: Pargament studies religious coping and problem-solving, not fine-grained contemplative instruction layers or cross-tradition transfer.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction for custody, support locus, and claimant distribution.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:65:Unlike Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers, the surviving distinct claim is a split-source predictive rule: code where practice direction enters before reading outcomes, then test whether layer mismatch predicts warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects better than technique, tradition label, social ecology, teacher style, and clinical risk. The general idea that practice has layered direction is not original.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:69:Candidate: Bahiya's immediate release, Tannisho's non-practice Other Power, and Dogen's practice-realization collapse the model's tendency to locate direction in analyzable layers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:71:Why it strains the model: Bahiya receives a brief instruction and is said to be released immediately, so textual coding cannot show whether direction came from prior training, readiness, teacher authority, or the instruction itself. Tannisho denies self-owned practice calculation and assigns decisive efficacy to Other Power, so calling nembutsu a directed practice can distort the source. Dogen-style practice-realization refuses a clean sequence of practice first and result later, so layer location may be an analyst imposition.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:73:Confidence effect: This lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model remains useful as a coding heuristic only if it includes analyst-frame-refused, no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, and undecidable values.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:77:- If: If direction layers have real explanatory force, split-source blind coders should infer warning and repair profiles from entry or instruction texts before reading manuals or interviews. Then: Layer scores should predict held-out warnings and repairs above baselines using tradition name, technique family, teacher style, social ecology, Pargament agency style, Lutz matrix dimensions, and VCE factors. Weakens if: Low inter-rater reliability, no predictive lift, or equally strong predictions from simpler baselines would weaken the model. Test surface: Six-case corpus: MN 10, Vivekachudamani, Tannisho, Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:106:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners provide concrete cases where a layer-coded mismatch predicts a repair that a generic technique, tradition, or clinical-risk model misses, for example when a noting-trained student applies deconstructive effort inside direct recognition, or when a Pure Land convert treats nembutsu as self-owned achievement despite instruction to entrust.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:124:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.78 to about 0.42. The useful contribution is not the broad claim that practices carry direction through many layers. That is strongly anticipated by primary texts, Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, situated learning, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The surviving extension is the pre-registered split-source test: code where direction enters, then predict warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:131:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited practice, practice-realization, radical Other Power, direct recognition, teacher-held, vow-held, grace-held, community-held, no-practice-frame, no-direction-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:133:- Compare predictive value against Dunne mindfulness styles, Lutz phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck grammar, Pargament agency styles, habitus and hysteresis, situated learning, VCE factors, teacher style, social ecology, intensity, and clinical-risk baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:136:- Use Bahiya, Tannisho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, direct introduction, and successful dual practice as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Manuals and teachers should warn against nihilism, dissociation, spiritual bypassing, false attainment, antinomianism, or ego-inflation in ways that match the path's self-management strategy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:61:    "Dogen practice-realization beginner original enlightenment Bendowa",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:105:      "source": "Dogen practice-realization sources, for example Soto and Bendowa summaries, https://zenlineage.org/schools/soto and https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:119:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners find that the rubric predicts real training differences and clarifies why premature self-dissolution, clinging to witness, bypassing, or false surrender fail differently across paths.",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:7:Status: draft
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:18:- Right effort, Other Power, direct introduction, and practice-realization differ by which functions are required and which owner is disallowed.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:26:- Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Other Power, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:28:Structural observation: SN 45.8 makes the practitioner the grammatical agent of desire, persistence, intent, prevention, abandonment, cultivation, and maintenance. Shinran's Letter to Senshin makes settled shinjin incompatible with calculation on the practicer's side, and says no working is true working. This comparison supports the function-claimant split: practice can retain necessary operations while changing who may claim them. But the split is already explicit in the primary materials, especially in Shinran, so the rubric mostly generalizes an old tension rather than discovering it.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The closest structural gap is not self-power versus other-power, which is well known, but the per-function grid of support locus plus prohibited claimant. Still, Pargament's religious coping styles, religious locus of control, Christian monergism and synergism, Sri Vaishnava markata and marjara, Buddhist upaya, Engler's ego-strength thesis, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger work already occupy much of the architecture.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:36:- Pargament religious coping self-directing deferring collaborative God control
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:38:- Shinran Other Power self power calculation hakarai entrusting mind
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:41:- Dogen practice realization one Bendowa gaining idea
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:47:- Kenneth Pargament et al., religious coping styles, summarized in https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/ and https://link.springer.com/rwe/10.1007/978-3-030-24348-7_578: overlap: Very close structural neighbor. Pargament's self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already ask whether responsibility for change rests with the person, God, or both.; difference: The claimant rubric moves from coping and perceived control to soteriological practice functions, and adds the negative field of which owner is forbidden to claim a function.; novelty impact: High reduction. The main variable, allocation of responsibility, is already modeled empirically.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:49:- Shinran, Other Power and hakarai, https://shinranworks.com/glossary/ and https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/: overlap: Near exact for source-centered paths. Shinran already separates entrusting from self-powered calculation and treats the practicer's claim as the problem.; difference: The Lumenary idea generalizes this to multiple functions and traditions rather than keeping it inside Jodo Shinshu.; novelty impact: High reduction. The forbidden-claimant idea is strongly present in Shinran.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:58:Unlike Pargament, religious locus-of-control work, self-power and other-power debates, monergism and synergism, and the local capacity ledger, this idea says that each required practice function should be coded twice: where the function is operationally supported and which claimant the tradition forbids from owning it.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:62:Candidate: Chinul's sudden awakening and gradual cultivation, plus radical Jodo Shinshu Other Power.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:64:Why it strains the model: Chinul makes the same cultivation necessary after awakening but empty of production, so the claimant status changes by stage. Shinran makes even entrusting wholly Other Power, so calling vow, hearing, or trust a support locus may be an analyst's domestication of grace. These cases strain any clean grid that treats support and claimant as stable cells.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:84:- Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:91:Answers that reduce originality: Teachers say the rubric merely renames standard warnings, or psychologists say it is Pargament and locus-of-control language applied to contemplative texts. Practitioners find claimant language alien or misleading.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.57 to about 0.45. The prohibited-claimant column is useful, but the main structure is strongly anticipated by self-power and other-power, monergism and synergism, Pargament's religious coping styles, locus-of-control research, Sri Vaishnava grace-effort debates, and local capacity-ledger work.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:116:- Read Pargament et al. on religious problem-solving styles directly before claiming novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:118:- Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, especially SN 45.8, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Chinul, Longchen Rabjam, and Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:109:      "Meditation safety researchers familiar with VCE and Cheetah House work",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:115:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/mn/mn.022.than.html",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:116:      "Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:120:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:17:- Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra break the grid by rejecting an active owner who finishes and assigns custody.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:25:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:26:- Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:28:Structural observation: MN 22 assumes a practitioner can grasp the Dhamma rightly, use it for crossing, and then not hold it as a possession. Shinran's jinen-honi and Tannisho relocate efficacy to Other Power and repeatedly reject practicer calculation, making even discussion of no working liable to become another working. This is a strong primary-text basis for narrowing release advice by agency grammar. But it also shows the candidate's central insight is not new inside Shinran: one cannot release as self-power what was never self-power to begin with.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:30:Secondary literature gap: This audit did not read Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Chinese, or commentarial originals. It did not read full Lewin on middle voice, full Heidegger and Eckhart scholarship, full Pargament, full Hori, full Dogen scholarship, or Jodo Shinshu scholarship beyond accessible translations and summaries. No Shin, Soto, Rinzai, or Christian grace practitioners were interviewed.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:32:Risk of overread: High. 'Middle voice' is an analyst metaphor that may not map cleanly onto Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, or Chinese practice grammar. The active versus middle distinction may become a renamed self-power versus Other Power distinction, or it may hide stage shifts where effort and surrender coexist.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:37:- Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power no working is true working
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:38:- Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act self-power Other Power
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:40:- Pargament religious problem-solving self-directing collaborative deferring styles
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:46:- David Lewin, The middle voice in Eckhart and modern continental philosophy, https://strathprints.strath.ac.uk/56562/: overlap: Extremely close for the proposed new variable. Lewin explicitly treats mystical relinquishment of will through the middle voice, between activity and passivity.; difference: Lewin centers Eckhart and Heidegger, not Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, or a modern achievement-cohort practice screen.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. The grammatical-voice relocation is already present in academic theology and philosophy.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:47:- Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/: overlap: Direct primary near-neighbor. Shinran already denies practicer calculation and says no working is true working in Other Power.; difference: The candidate turns Shinran into a comparative diagnostic against universal release teachings.; novelty impact: Downgrades the slogan 'you cannot release what you never held' to a Shinran-compatible restatement.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:48:- Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/: overlap: Very close. Tannisho says nembutsu is not practice or good act for the practicer because it arises wholly from Other Power and is free of self-power.; difference: The candidate uses that structure to set a cohort boundary for modern achievement-driven practitioners.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade for the Other Power anomaly and self-power critique.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:50:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Very close for agency distribution. Self-directing, collaborative, and deferring styles already distinguish personal agency, exchange with God, and waiting for divine action.; difference: Pargament studies coping style, not method completion or release of practice results.; novelty impact: Downgrades agency novelty. The candidate must show voice coding predicts beyond Pargament-style agency coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:57:Unlike Lewin on middle voice, Shinran on Other Power, Dogen on practice-realization, Pargament on religious coping styles, Heart Sutra no-attainment reliance, Smith, Sells, and prior Lumenary completion models, this idea's possible contribution is a testable fit rule: give release-the-method advice only to practitioners whose own language shows active earning and result-ownership, then test whether the advice helps them more than it helps other-power, nondual, or practice-realization practitioners.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:63:Why it strains the model: If most actual paths shift voices by stage, role, and context, then active versus middle voice will not sort traditions or predict guidance. Pure Land practitioners still say the nembutsu, Zen practitioners still sit, Christian grace traditions still discipline attention, and high-striving nondual practitioners may still benefit from release advice despite no-owner doctrine.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:65:Confidence effect: Keeps the idea at extended. It can only rise if voice coding predicts warnings, confusion, and repair better than self-power, Other Power, Pargament agency style, teacher style, and clinical-risk baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:70:- If: Grammatical voice predicts practice guidance better than custody-grid coding. Then: Blind coding of completion-talk as active, middle, passive, mixed, or no-voice predicts held-out warnings, repairs, and supervision needs better than retain, release, embody categories alone. Weakens if: Custody values, tradition identity, teacher style, institution type, or Pargament agency styles predict guidance as well as or better than voice coding. Test surface: Split-source codebook tested on MN 22, Tannisho, Dogen, Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, Christian grace texts, and practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:71:- If: The embodied-without-ownership cell is too elastic. Then: Coders will overuse embodied-without-ownership for Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, Dzogchen, apophasis, and other hard cases, with low inter-rater reliability and weak prediction of warnings. Weakens if: The cell has clear boundaries, high inter-rater reliability, and predicts concrete repairs better than voice coding. Test surface: Inter-rater trial comparing the old two-axis grid against active, middle, passive, and mixed voice labels.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:87:- Does voice coding change guidance beyond older labels such as self-power, Other Power, grace, surrender, non-attainment, or Pargament coping style?
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:89:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say the claim is simply self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, practice-realization, or middle-voice theology in new language, and that it does not change sequencing, warning, or repair.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:109:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.39. The strongest prior-art pressure is Lewin's middle-voice analysis plus Shinran's explicit Other Power and Pargament's agency styles. Human-condition fit is strong but narrow: high-striving people with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, comparison, and result-ownership. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, people in grace-centered or nondual practice who do not experience ownership, and people whose distress is caused mainly by structural exploitation rather than self-rating.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:114:- Search and read full Lewin, Pargament, Dogen scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Gelassenheit, and middle-voice theology before raising novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md:116:- Create a voice-coding sheet with values for active, middle, passive, mixed-by-stage, simultaneous-mixed, no-owner, no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-ad.md:24:I concede four things cleanly. First, the distributed-containment model is genuinely better at explaining other-power, devotional, and teacher-field traditions; the original model underweighted these. Second, Engler's clinical formulation covers the safety ground and has priority on the practical insight. Third, the title overstated universality; the claim is graded, not universal. Fourth, the four management strategies are heuristic mixtures, not clean types. What I defend is more specific. The distributed-containment model and the minimum-self model are not competitors. They answer different questions, and the containment model presupposes the functional one. You cannot distribute continuity until you know what must be continued. The functions are: receiving instruction or transmission, sustaining effort or openness, correcting error, and recognizing change. Where these are housed is a second-order question. The irreducible receiving surface is not trivially true. Traditions that push it thinnest, Dzogchen and radical Pure Land, develop the most precise protocols around exactly that thin point. Dzogchen requires a specific relational context, precise timing, and teacher judgment of readiness. Shinran developed elaborate doctrinal machinery to explain how even entrusting is given without self-power. If the receiving surface were trivial, these traditions would not need to engineer around it so carefully. The Engler formulation is sequential: first build ego, then dissolve. The revised minimum-self model is concurrent: a beginning vipassana practitioner needs enough self to sit and follow instructions while those instructions are already framing the self as impersonal aggregates. This is not a before-and-after problem but a during problem that the practice manages at every session. The management strategies, even as heuristics, predict architecture that the containment model alone does not. Tell me a tradition's primary continuity strategy and I can predict its map type, warning profile, and verification method. Causal continuity yields condition-tracking maps (Abhidharma). Ontological identity yields confusion-accounting theory (adhyasa). Temporal collapse resists stage sequencing (Dogen). Divine restoration concentrates teacher authority at the annihilation moment (Sufi sheikh at fana). These predictions require knowing both what continuity function is at stake and what the dissolution target is. Container strength alone cannot generate them. The human-condition revision: the model matters most for people encountering dissolution teachings outside traditional containers. When the container is strong, the practitioner's receiving surface can be thin because the ecology carries load. When the container is weak or absent (app-based meditation, books without teachers, retreat weekends without follow-up, psychedelic experiences without integration), the practitioner's own self-capacity must carry more of the continuity burden. The danger zone is the mismatch: a person with low self-capacity entering a path with weak distributed support, or a person with high self-management entering a strongly distributed path that demands a surrender they cannot give. The primary cohort is secular seekers, trauma survivors drawn to dissolution language, high-achievers approaching practice with optimization mindsets, cross-tradition samplers without sustained teacher relationships, and clinicians or chaplains who need to assess when practice helps versus harms. The non-fit case is practitioners in intact traditional communities where the distributed ecology already manages continuity; for them, the model adds nothing. Also outside scope: acute psychiatric crisis (clinical stabilization, not contemplative architecture) and single-lineage practitioners whose receiving surface and dissolution target are always aligned by design. The deepest crux is whether function-identification adds predictive power beyond placement-identification. If knowing w...
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:28:Structural observation: SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The search found strong near-neighbors in transfer-of-training theory, Barnett and Ceci's far-transfer taxonomy, Hadot on school-shaped spiritual exercises, Katz on tradition-conditioned experience, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Pargament on agency allocation, situated learning, Buddhist upaya, and VCE adverse-effects coding. It did not yet close-read full books by Hadot, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Lave and Wenger, or Pargament, and it did not code actual cross-training cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:42:- Pargament religion problem solving process three styles coping self directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:45:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:55:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency allocation between practitioner and sacred source, especially self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles.; difference: The candidate treats agency allocation as one layer in a broader transfer-failure model rather than as the primary typology.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction, especially for claimant and support-locus claims.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:62:Unlike transfer theory, Hadot, Katz, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says grain is only the predictive surplus of a prior dissolution target after rehearsed operation and receiving claimant grammar have already explained what they can.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:124:- Compare predictive value against transfer theory, situated learning, Hadot, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.json:124:    "Close-read Tannisho chapter 1, Orange canons 3-7, SN 55.5, Mencius 2A6, Longchenpa Trekcho, and a Yogacara transformation-of-basis source before publication.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.json:157:    "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The model may project a philosophical bootstrapping problem onto practitioners who begin through family, ritual, obedience, attraction, crisis, community, or habit without experiencing a paradox. It may also collapse distinct cases: Shinran's Other Power and Orange's prevenient grace are structurally close, while Dzogchen self-disclosure and Platonic recollection may be closer than the typology admits.",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:7:Status: draft
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:11:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:23:- Dialogue turn 3 reflexive objection from Shinran's jinen honi and the need for self-limitation
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:58:- Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.
