reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:164:      "Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:168:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully reread Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Wilber, Engler's full chapter context, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen and Mahamudra manuals, or Britton's full adverse-effects corpus. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Burmese terms were not checked directly. Stronger novelty would require split-source coding and practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:169:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the five aggregates, yet the discourse depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and a sequence from seeing to disenchantment and release. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 refuses ordinary objectification of the seer and knower, but authorizes the remainder as the inner ruler and Self. Tannisho relocates efficacy away from self-power into Amida's vow and entrusting, while also preserving teacher lineage, warning against license, and refusing ownership of disciples. Mahasi's Manual of Insight makes operational remainder unusually explicit: ethical preparation, concentration, noting, progress mapping, teacher interpretation, and verification are all part of the practice surface. The close read supports the three variables, but also shows that much of the structure is already visible in primary materials."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:178:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike VCE, Britton's adverse-effects work, Engler, Pargament, Lindbeck, Asad, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating contemplative paths can be coded along three independent axes, operational capacity, residue policy, and training ecology, and that the interaction among those axes will predict safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns better than any one axis alone."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:27:- Tannisho, sections 1, 6, 10, and 11, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:29:- Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:32:Structural observation: The primary texts support an interaction field but also reduce originality. Tannisho makes entry depend on entrusting to Amida's vow, relocates decisive efficacy to Other Power, and warns against self-power, teacher ownership, and self-will. SN 22.59 negates ownership of the five aggregates and moves through disenchantment, release, and knowledge of release, without authorizing a hidden self as remainder. Dogen strains the sequence because practice and realization are one, so beginning and fruit cannot be cleanly separated. The Gita complicates the model by mixing action, multiple causes, divine inner rulership, and final surrender, so one text may contain several entry-residue logics by chapter and voice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:34:Secondary literature gap: This audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, rites of passage, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, situated learning, Pure Land Other Power, Christian grace, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:43:- "religion problem solving process" Pargament self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:45:- "Tannisho" Other Power self-power Primal Vow chapter 11
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:46:- "Dogen" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:57:- Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for distributing agency between person and God through self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles, and for predicting different outcomes from that distribution.; difference: Pargament studies religious coping, not entry into transformative practice after self-negation, nor source-layer coding of residue.; novelty impact: High reduction for support-locus and effort-theory claims.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:58:- Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Near exact for vow-held entry, blocked self-credit, warning against self-power, and transformation disclosed through entrusting.; difference: Tannisho is one tradition-internal case, not a cross-tradition predictive rubric.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for Pure Land examples and strong pressure against recoding Other Power as practitioner capacity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:66:Unlike Rambo, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, VCE, Shinran, Dogen, Orange, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the key test is additive prediction: independently coded residue authorization and entry grammar should interact to predict held-out safeguards, warnings, effort theories, verification rules, and repairs better than entry-only, residue-only, agency-style, social-ecology, tradition-identity, or source-layer baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:78:- If: If entry-residue interaction is real, split-source coding of entry texts and residue doctrine should predict later warning clusters better than entry grammar or residue policy alone. Then: Vow-held or grace-held entries should warn against self-credit and effort appropriation. No-self entries should warn against nihilism, dissociation, or reification. Self-inquiry entries should warn against objectifying the witness. Practice-realization entries should warn against instrumentalizing practice. Weakens if: Warnings are predicted equally well by generic tradition identity, teacher style, Pargament agency style, Rambo conversion stage, VCE factors, or social ecology, with no incremental gain from the interaction term. Test surface: Blind-coded corpus with entry passages, separate residue passages, and held-out manuals or practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:105:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say the framework is obvious as self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, upaya, conversion stages, or doctrine-as-grammar, and it would not alter sequencing, warning, verification, or repair. They cannot identify cases where the interaction predicts more than teacher experience, tradition identity, social context, or clinical risk.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:125:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The synthesis is useful and testable, but most components have strong near-neighbors: conversion theory for entry process, rites-of-passage theory for thresholds, Lindbeck for grammar, Pargament for agency distribution, Shinran and Orange for vow or grace-held beginnings, Dogen for practice-realization collapse, VCE for factor-separated contemplative outcomes, and prior Lumenary audits for residue, first-break, entry-state, threshold grammar, claimability, support, and operational remainder ecology. The remaining contribution is a split-source interaction test with additive predictive burden.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:133:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, radical Other Power, ritual-first entry, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:134:- Compare predictive power against Rambo conversion stages, Lofland-Stark conversion conditions, Van Gennep and Turner liminality, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament agency styles, Lave and Wenger situated learning, upaya, religious socialization, VCE factor coding, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-a-tradition-s-dissolution-target-independently-predict-where-contin.md:24:I concede more than I expected. The challenger is right that 'minimum self' over-internalizes the operative continuity, that residue policy is a genuine variable my model lacked, and that other-power traditions expose a real weakness in my original framing. These are not minor adjustments. But the core insight survives in revised form. Even Shinran's practitioner, who contributes nothing but shinjin, must be the kind of being that can receive shinjin. Receptivity is thinner than agency, but it is irreducibly internal. A rock in the temple does not receive the nembutsu. A dog hearing the chanting does not entrust. Whatever shinjin is, it requires a being structured to be addressed by it. More importantly, the challenger's model treats distribution and residue as independent variables, but I think distribution is downstream of what the teaching dissolves. Jodo Shinshu externalizes continuity to Amida's vow precisely because its teaching negates self-powered agency. Advaita internalizes continuity to Atman precisely because its teaching negates the empirical person while preserving ultimate identity. Dogen compresses continuity into the present precisely because his teaching negates the temporal gap between practice and realization. If these correspondences hold across traditions, the dissolution target is the generative pressure that determines where continuity must migrate. The challenger's model is richer than mine in vocabulary but poorer in causal structure. So I revise: the operative concept is not minimum self but minimum receptivity, which is the irreducible internal capacity to be addressed and transformed. Beyond that floor, each tradition requires additional capacities in proportion to how much of the work it assigns to the practitioner rather than to external supports. The distribution of continuity is constrained by the scope of negation. The residue policy is a genuine third variable that completes the model. The crux is whether distribution follows from dissolution or floats free. That is an empirical question about the actual architecture of contemplative paths, and the paired-tradition test I describe would settle it.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-a-tradition-s-dissolution-target-independently-predict-where-contin.md:30:The revision is transformed, and in several respects improved. It no longer forces all traditions into a self-powered contemplative frame, and it rightly treats Shinran, grace, vow, teacher, and community as serious carriers of continuity. I would not call it simply stronger, because the original claim's central noun has been surrendered. A minimum self has become minimum receptivity plus distributed continuity plus residue policy. That is a different model, not just a repaired version of the old one. The strongest surviving insight is that negation creates architectural pressure. If a path negates self-powered agency, it will likely move continuity toward vow, grace, teacher, or communal form. If it negates the empirical person while preserving ultimate identity, it will likely locate continuity in a deeper ontological layer. That is a good causal hypothesis. But it still has to compete with a historical one: traditions may first develop concrete practices, institutions, devotional habits, and authority structures, then formulate doctrines that rationalize where continuity already sits. So the named crux is nearly right, but should be sharpened. The question is not only whether distribution follows from dissolution or varies independently. The question is whether dissolution target predicts distribution after rival explanations are controlled. If it does, the proponent's transformed model becomes genuinely strong. If it does not, minimum receptivity remains a true but thin floor, and the better explanatory unit is the full continuity ecology of a path.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:25:- Tannisho, BDK translation, especially chapters 1 to 3, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:28:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-realization passage, https://justdharma.org/practice-and-enlightenment-dogen-zenji/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:30:Structural observation: Tannisho gives a vow-held entry grammar: the decisive threshold is firm entrusting in Amida's vow, with warnings against self-effort, esoteric seeking, and arbitrary interpretation. Orange gives a grace-first Christian entry grammar: even prayer, will, desire, faith, and assent are preceded by grace, so anti-Pelagian safeguards are structurally expected. SN 55.5 gives a different threshold grammar: association with admirable people, hearing true Dhamma, appropriate attention, and practice in accordance with Dhamma. It predicts safeguards around community, teaching, attention, and right practice, not grace or vow. Dogen's Bendowa strains the model because practice and realization are not two sequential states; the warning is against waiting for enlightenment outside practice. These texts support the idea that entry accounts predict warning profiles, but they also show high translation strain: grace, vow, stream-entry, and practice-realization are not interchangeable values of one neutral variable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:46:- Tannisho Primal Vow entrusting no other good self effort
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:49:- Dogen Bendowa practice enlightenment are one beginner practice original enlightenment
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:81:- If: Entry grammar has incremental predictive force after controls. Then: Coders using only entry texts can predict later beginner warnings better after adding first-break type to models that already include anthropology, authority, conversion process, ritual inheritance, socialization, and practice ecology. Weakens if: First-break type adds little or no predictive gain, or all signal is absorbed by Rambo-style conversion variables, OCIA-style initiation structure, institutional authority, teacher relation, or practice intensity. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Tannisho, Orange, SN 55.5, OCIA texts, Dogen, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra entry manual, and one Sufi or Christian contemplative initiation source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:92:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin and Other Power
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:16:- Comparison must first preserve the transformation register, such as human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, or causal continuity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:25:- Shinran, Tannisho, especially chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11, trans. Taitetsu Unno, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, especially sections 3, 4, 7, and 10, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:28:Structural observation: The Tannisho strongly supports the register-first move. Its decisive register is Other Power, and it names boundary failures such as self-power, calculation, doubt, wrong teacher ownership, and confusing nembutsu with the practitioner's own good act. Bendowa is the anomaly case. It names wrong understanding, false teachers, verbal clinging, and inadequate practice, but its register is practice-realization, where training and enlightenment are not two. The proposed model reads Shinran well, but its interface language strains Dogen because an interface can imply the very separation between practitioner, practice, and realization that Bendowa rejects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The closest scholarly prior art includes Oliver Freiberger on comparison as selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation; Paul Hedges on comparative theology and hermeneutics; Francis Clooney's comparative theology; Katz and Sharf on contextualist and anti-experience-flattening method; Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model; and Pargament's religious problem-solving styles. The audit did not fully close-read Clooney, Lindbeck, Dzogchen root texts, Meister Eckhart, Qushayri, Ibn Arabi, or Shinran's letters. That gap prevents any candidate-discovery claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:36:- Tannisho chapter 11 self power calculation Other Power text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:37:- Tannisho chapter 8 nembutsu not practice good act Shinran pdf
