reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:62:    "Dogen practice realization verification Genjokoan Bendowa",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:64:    "Tannisho Other Power Original Vow no practice no good teacher maturity faith"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:100:      "overlap": "Close single-tradition prior. Hori shows ritual formalism and mystical insight working together in Rinzai training, which anticipates the link between method, testing, teacher authority, and transmission.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:101:      "source": "G. Victor Sogen Hori, Teaching and learning in the Rinzai Zen monastery, Cambridge record, https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/abs/teaching-and-learning-in-japan/teaching-and-learning-in-the-rinzai-zen-monastery/06E010651A6042E1FF3EC9BE242460D9"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:104:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and God-related agency, not contemplative boundary operations after self-weakening practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:107:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, accessible summary, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:119:      "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:133:    "Add mandatory values for no-threshold, practice-realization, retained method, released method, self-undermining method, embodied method, radical Other Power, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, community-held, Prajnaparamita-held, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, inherited practice, apophatic refusal, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:134:    "Compare predictive value against Asad discursive tradition, Lindbeck grammar, Weberian authority, Sharf and Katz contextualism, Pargament agency styles, upaya pedagogy, VCE variables, institution type, teacher style, social ecology, clinical risk, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:136:    "Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:140:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.42. The exact language is fresh, but both axes and much of the predictive burden are already present in prior Lumenary records: Method's Reckoning, Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, and related entry and support ledgers. External prior art also strongly anticipates the components: Asad and Lindbeck for native authority and grammar, Sharf and Katz-style contextualism for suspicion of experience-first comparison, Hori for Zen training and verification, Pargament for agency distribution, VCE for multidimensional contemplative difficulty coding, MN 22 for validated-then-released method, Heart Sutra for no-attainment plus reliance, Tannisho for Other Power custody, and Dogen for practice-realization anomaly. The surviving value is a bounded split-source interaction test, not a doctrine candidate or strong original discovery.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:154:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:161:      "Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament's agency and coping work"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:166:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:168:      "Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:169:      "Tannisho, BDK English Tripitaka translation, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:171:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:172:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:173:    "structural_observation": "The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:182:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Hori, Pargament, VCE research, MN 22, the Heart Sutra, and prior Lumenary authority and custody ledgers, this idea's surviving distinct claim is a narrow interaction protocol: code boundary operation and custody rule independently, then test whether their interaction predicts held-out verification, teaching permission, warning, repair, and reentry patterns better than doctrine, tradition label, stage, institution, boundary alone, or custody alone. Without that split-source predictive gain, it is mostly a consolidation of prior work."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:19:- Release of the raft should not mean release of correction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:25:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Thanissaro translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:28:Structural observation: MN 22 is already a strong source for this structure. Arittha's private interpretation is challenged by monks and then by the Buddha before the raft simile appears, and the text pairs right grasp with later release. Ignatius gives an even closer practitioner rule: after a consolation, later resolutions and opinions need examination before being trusted. Together they already contain the core pattern, experience or method may be valid, but interpretation still needs correction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:30:Secondary literature gap: This audit did not read full Cassian, Evagrius, Teresa of Avila, John of the Cross, Jonathan Edwards, contemporary spiritual-direction manuals, full Hori, full Katz, full Sharf, or Cheetah House materials. No teachers, clinicians, or solo practitioners were interviewed.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:36:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta raft simile right grasp wrong interpretation Arittha
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:41:- spiritual bypassing Welwood spiritual practice avoids unresolved emotional issues
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:42:- Dogen practice realization correction teacher community Bendowa Genjokoan
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:46:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html: overlap: Very close. The sutta joins wrong-grasp correction, teacher and sangha challenge, right use of Dhamma, and later release of the raft.; difference: The candidate generalizes this into a cross-tradition correction-holder rule and a modern solo-practitioner practice.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. The release plus correction structure is already primary-text material.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:56:Unlike MN 22, Ignatian discernment, VCE, James, Asad, Lindbeck, Sells, and the prior Lumenary recognition-gap audit, this idea's possible contribution is a narrow safety heuristic: after method release, verify that some trustworthy correction path remains, and test whether naming that path reduces inflation, shame, and isolated overinterpretation without increasing dependency.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:77:- Meditation safety clinicians familiar with VCE or Cheetah House work
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md:79:- Clinicians working with scrupulosity, dissociation, anxiety, and spiritual bypassing
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen's Bendowa denies a clean boundary in realization and denies a beginning in practice. Inherited religious participation can also preserve continuity before any explicit self-negating doctrine is consciously adopted. In both cases, the model may impose a migration story where the tradition presents no transfer, no threshold, or no separate continuity problem."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.json:42:      "test_surface": "Historical comparison of Shinran communities, Soto monastic practice, Theravada reform movements, modern mindfulness programs, and Christian grace controversies.",
