reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:117:      "difference": "Shinran gives a specific Pure Land case, while the candidate proposes a cross-tradition entry and claimant grammar with prediction tests.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:118:      "novelty_impact": "High reduction and high anomaly pressure. The candidate may mostly generalize Shinran and grace patterns into coding language.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:119:      "overlap": "Very close for load relocation and forbidden claimant. Shinran's Other Power grammar denies self-power as the decisive basis of liberation and relocates decisive function to the Vow and Name.",
