reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:146:    "Run a comparison against baseline models: Rambo conversion stages, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, upaya capacity pedagogy, liminality, situated learning, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity ledger.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:151:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.72 to about 0.58. The idea is not a discovery-level concept. Its entry ecology is strongly anticipated by Rambo, Berger, liminality, situated learning, and religious socialization. Its grammar language is anticipated by Lindbeck. Its agency distribution is anticipated by Pargament and grace or Other Power sources. Its support-locus and safeguard rubric is very close to prior Lumenary Entry-State Ledger, Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant, and Credit Distribution records. The remaining contribution is an extension: an independence audit that tries to prevent construct leakage between entry doctrine, claimant rule, anthropology, safeguard, and verification.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:164:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:177:      "Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, translation by Taitetsu Unno, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:179:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The phrase grammar risks renaming Lindbeck, Rambo, Pargament, Berger, religious socialization theory, and Lumenary's own Entry-State Ledger unless the candidate produces non-circular coding fields and predictive wins. It also risks imposing analyst-owned agency language on traditions that explicitly refuse the claimant frame.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:180:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:181:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 parses the path through practitioner-cultivated functions: right view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The grammar permits the practitioner to perform decisive training functions, though under Buddhist doctrinal constraints. Tannisho shifts decisive efficacy away from self-power and toward entrusting, Other Power, and the Primal Vow, while also warning against claiming disciples or treating nembutsu as self-owned practice or merit. This supports the candidate's entry-claimant link. It also shows the main risk: the same Shinran material supplies entry grammar, claimant prohibition, danger, and verification language at once, so a prediction test can easily become circular."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:190:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo's conversion-process model, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar model, Pargament's religious agency styles, Berger's plausibility structures, upaya pedagogy, liminality theory, Shinran's Other Power grammar, Orange grace theology, religious socialization theory, and Lumenary's Entry-State Ledger, this idea claims that entry mechanism and forbidden claimant form one testable agency grammar, and that a split-source independence audit can determine whether that grammar predicts safeguards and verification practices without circularly reusing the same text as both cause and evidence."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:11:    "The model distinguishes a bypassing state from a compulsive self-scoring state.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:26:  "exact_claim": "A practice-routing model must decide three things before recommending a return test: whether the practice permits result language, whether the practitioner is presently bypassing or self-scoring, and who should hold the diagnostic gate. Self-administered return attention may help the bypasser who uses insight to avoid conduct. For the compulsive scorer, the gate should be externally held by a teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or replaced by resultless practice. For oscillators, the assignment must be state-level and revisable, not a stable identity label.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:30:      "expected_observation": "Split-source coding will show that texts coded as instrumental from doctrinal or instruction passages contain more held-out return, fruit, stewardship, or conduct-test warnings, while Dogen and Shinran-style non-instrumental cases contain more form, vow, no-calculation, or practice-realization correction language.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:32:      "test_surface": "Blind coding of Ignatius, MN 22, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho, Rinzai koan training, apophatic Christian texts, Sufi fana and baqa sources, and modern practice manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:42:      "expected_observation": "Within-person diary or EMA data will show the same practitioner moving between bypassing and scoring states across contexts, and state-level routing will predict next-day outcomes better than a one-time trait classification.",
