reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:63:    "spiritual bypassing Picciotto Fox Neto phenomenology psychological avoidance spiritualizing",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:90:      "difference": "Pargament concerns coping with God and individual agency, not diagnostic gate custody across teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:93:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion 1988, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:96:      "difference": "The source does not address spiritual return tests, result-language scope, or bypassing versus self-scoring states.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:117:      "source": "Spiritual bypassing literature, for example Picciotto, Fox, and Neto, A phenomenology of spiritual bypass, Journal of Spirituality in Mental Health 2018, indexed at https://openurl.ebsco.com/fulltext/gcd%3A132497915, and Fox and Picciotto, https://brill.com/view/journals/cvj/64/2/article-p227_7.xml"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:132:    "Read full sources before public use: Ignatian directorial literature, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, Pargament, measurement-based care, guided self-help, rumination and self-focused attention, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and scrupulosity ERP.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:137:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.42. The gate-holder idea is already close to Ignatian discernment, spiritual direction, contemplative adverse-effects support, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, Pargament agency styles, and OCD reassurance literature. The surviving contribution is narrower: a Lumenary safety-routing heuristic that combines result-language permission, current bypassing or scoring state, and diagnostic custody. Human-condition fit is real but bounded. It is for functioning high achievers, founders, students, creators, professionals, and spiritual practitioners who either use insight to avoid conduct or convert practice into proof of worth. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, coercive workloads, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive communities, or people without trustworthy support.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:163:      "Shinran, On Jinen Honi, and Dogen shusho itto summary, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/ and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:166:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit did not read full Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, full Dogen Bendowa or Eihei Shingi, Shinran and Tannisho in Japanese, OCD scrupulosity treatment literature beyond abstracts, or the full measurement-based care and guided self-help literatures. It also needs direct work in perfectionism, achievement-contingent self-worth, and contemplative adverse effects before public practice guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:167:    "structural_observation": "Ignatius already makes gate custody explicit. The exercitant reports movements and thoughts, the director adapts exercises, and disclosure to a confessor or spiritual person breaks the secrecy of deceptive movements. Yet Annotation 15 also limits the director, the guide is not supposed to seize the final choice. Shinran strains the model from the opposite side: jinen honi rejects practicer calculation and warns that even talking about no-working can become another form of working. Dogen also strains the return-test frame because practice and realization are not separated as cause and later product. The candidate's structure is therefore not a discovery at the primary-text level. Its possible contribution is a routing rule for deciding when Ignatian-style disclosure, clinical support, fixed-rule gating, or no-result practice is appropriate."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:176:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE person-centered support, Pargament agency styles, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, spiritual bypassing literature, and prior Lumenary return and scope-gate models, this claim says a public practice instruction should pass through three ordered gates: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and custody of the diagnostic itself. Its novelty depends on whether that three-gate routing predicts harm, repair, or non-fit better than existing spiritual direction, clinical triage, and contemplative-safety frameworks."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:21:    "prediction": "Therapies with similar techniques but different agency-frame stance should produce different failure modes. Agency-strengthening models should risk self-blame, surrender-based models should risk passivity, self-dissolving models should risk dissociation or avoidance, and already-whole models should risk bypassing concrete behavioral repair.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:43:      "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews, adverse-practice reports, and comparison with spiritual-bypassing literature.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:44:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "These cases are no more common than in regulatory traditions, or spiritual bypassing explains them without reference to ontological claimability."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:56:    "Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles self-directing deferring collaborative",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:59:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:65:    "spiritual bypassing nondual premature realization claims"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:78:      "source": "Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:90:      "source": "Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:135:    "Compare predictive power against Lindbeck grammar, Pargament agency styles, upaya pedagogy, grace-effort theology, spiritual bypassing literature, prior Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, and Entry-Claimant Grammar.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:136:    "Use Longchenpa Trekcho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, Pure Land Other Power, Srivaishnava prapatti, and successful cross-training as anomaly tests rather than confirming examples.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:140:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.60. The idea is not a discovery of anti-appropriation, non-doership, practice-realization, already-attained realization, grace-effort distribution, or stage-dependent cultivation. Those are well anticipated by primary texts, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary records. The remaining contribution is a novel synthesis: claimability stance as a prior validity check for support-locus and forbidden-claimant coding.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:143:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is ordinary doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, upaya, grace-effort theology, nondual pedagogy, spiritual bypassing, or prior Lumenary ledger language. Dissolutive and ontological teachers reject the rubric as reifying. Teachers cannot produce stance-specific repairs beyond familiar cautions against pride, laziness, premature claims, or poor integration.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:157:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:161:      "Contemplative clinicians familiar with spiritual bypassing and adverse meditation effects"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:167:      "Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:170:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Search reached Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lindbeck on doctrine as rule or grammar, Dogen practice-realization sources, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Chinul sudden awakening and gradual cultivation, Srivaishnava prapatti debates, Gita action-doership passages, Shinran Other Power, and upaya literature. It did not fully close-read Lindbeck's full book, Pargament's full 1988 article, Tibetan commentarial material on direct introduction, Sanskrit Advaita sources on praptasya prapti, or Srivaishnava primary polemics. This blocks candidate-discovery status.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:171:    "structural_observation": "MMK 8 attacks any independently established agent-action structure. Bendowa collapses a simple before-after relation between practice and realization, while still insisting on concrete sitting, teacher transmission, and trust. Together they support the candidate's warning that prohibition language can distort dissolutive traditions. They also reduce novelty, because the anti-appropriation move is primary-textual rather than newly discovered. The possible contribution is the comparative coding rule: do not use forbidden claimant until the tradition's claimability grammar has been identified."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.json:180:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's religious agency styles, Nagarjuna's agent-action critique, Dogen's practice-realization, Dzogchen primordial purity, Advaita praptasya prapti, Srivaishnava effort-grace debates, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary credit-distribution records, this idea says the first coding question is whether the claiming framework itself is authorized, dissolved, ontologically denied, or stage-dependent. Its possible contribution is not the anti-appropriation insight, but the rule that support-locus and forbidden-claimant rubrics are valid only after that prior stance is coded."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and successful ordinary ethical practice without a marked peak experience.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Prevents candidate-discovery status. The model is useful as a heuristic only if it can code no-threshold, no-peak, Other Power, inherited practice, and practice-realization without forcing them into a modern after-experience frame.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases resist the sequence of method, result, and return. Dogen makes practice and realization inseparable. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow and can make nembutsu non-practice from the practitioner's side. Inherited religion may not have a discrete completion event. Ordinary ethical formation may return without peak experience at all."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:12:    "Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:41:      "expected_observation": "Practitioners trained in Advaita inquiry, Prajnaparamita practice, raft-style early Buddhist training, and Soto practice-realization will describe different appropriate relations to insight: stable recognition, resisted attainment, released tool, or ongoing practice-conduct identity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:50:    "\"raft simile\" \"not for holding onto\" MN 22 method release",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:54:    "\"Dogen\" \"practice and realization are one\" Bendowa",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:59:      "difference": "The candidate broadens the raft logic into a three-way return rubric and applies it to achievement-contingent self-worth.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:61:      "overlap": "Direct primary near-neighbor. It already gives a method-use test: use the raft to cross, then do not carry it as possession.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:62:      "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/mn/mn.022.than.html"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:66:      "novelty_impact": "Downgrades novelty but supports the model's refusal to make raft-release universal.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:74:      "source": "Dogen Bendowa material, Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:104:    "Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited religion, no-threshold practice, no-peak ethical formation, direct recognition, and clinician-held support.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:106:    "Close-read Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Rinzai koan curriculum source, Cloud of Unknowing or Dionysius, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising source reliability."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:108:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.58 to 0.41. The teaching line is strong and publishable only as a restrained synthesis for achievement-contingent self-worth. The research model should be treated as extended prior art until it predicts warnings, repairs, or return duties better than existing upaya, raft, apophatic, practice-realization, spiritual-exercises, VCE, authority, and grammar frameworks.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:111:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Teachers recognize the rubric as ordinary raft teaching, upaya, practice-realization, apophatic unsaying, koan curriculum, spiritual exercise, aftercare, or ethics of fruits, and say it does not predict guidance beyond existing lineage rules.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:119:      "Theravada monastics and lay teachers familiar with MN 22 and raft simile",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:123:      "Jodo Shinshu teachers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:130:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/mn/mn.022.than.html",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:134:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit found strong near-neighbors in Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Sells on unsaying, Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, VCE, Hadot-style spiritual exercises, Zen oxherding return motifs, and Buddhist raft or upaya literature. It did not read the full books by Smith, Sells, Hadot, Hori, Lindbeck, Katz, or Sharf, and it did not consult original Sanskrit, Pali, Chinese, Japanese, Greek, Latin, Arabic, or Tibetan.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:135:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:147:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:25:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:27:- Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:28:- Tannisho, BDK English Tripitaka translation, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:41:- G. Victor Sogen Hori Koan and Kensho in the Rinzai Zen Curriculum teacher testing
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:44:- Pargament religion problem-solving self-directing deferring collaborative coping agency God practitioner
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:45:- Dogen practice realization verification Genjokoan Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:47:- Tannisho Other Power Original Vow no practice no good teacher maturity faith
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:56:- G. Victor Sogen Hori, Teaching and learning in the Rinzai Zen monastery, Cambridge record, https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/abs/teaching-and-learning-in-japan/teaching-and-learning-in-the-rinzai-zen-monastery/06E010651A6042E1FF3EC9BE242460D9: overlap: Close single-tradition prior. Hori shows ritual formalism and mystical insight working together in Rinzai training, which anticipates the link between method, testing, teacher authority, and transmission.; difference: It is not a cross-tradition two-axis model.; novelty impact: High reduction for Zen evidence and for any claim that verification architecture is newly noticed.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:57:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, accessible summary, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency and custody distribution across human and divine roles: self-directing, deferring, and collaborative patterns already formalize different responsibility allocations.; difference: Pargament studies coping and God-related agency, not contemplative boundary operations after self-weakening practice.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. Custody rules need baseline comparison against established religious agency models.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:59:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html: overlap: Very close primary-text prior for boundary operation. The method is useful for crossing but not for holding onto afterward.; difference: The text is not a general comparative taxonomy and does not add custody recipients beyond the Dhamma's proper use.; novelty impact: High reduction for the method-validates-then-releases structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:64:Unlike Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Hori, Pargament, VCE research, MN 22, the Heart Sutra, and prior Lumenary authority and custody ledgers, this idea's surviving distinct claim is a narrow interaction protocol: code boundary operation and custody rule independently, then test whether their interaction predicts held-out verification, teaching permission, warning, repair, and reentry patterns better than doctrine, tradition label, stage, institution, boundary alone, or custody alone. Without that split-source predictive gain, it is mostly a consolidation of prior work.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:68:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization identity, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and apophatic refusal in Dionysius.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:70:Why it strains the model: Dogen removes the gap between method and result, so there may be no threshold where boundary and custody can be assigned. Tannisho places decisive working in Amida's vow while warning against self-calculation, so calling entrusting a local custody handoff can reintroduce the self-power frame the text resists. Inherited religion may mature by continuity and ritual participation rather than by a discernible handoff. Dionysius places the divine Cause beyond affirmation and negation, which destabilizes God as a simple custody recipient.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:72:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs mandatory no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited continuity, apophatic refusal, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, and analyst-frame-refused values.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:86:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:93:- Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament's agency and coping work
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.42. The exact language is fresh, but both axes and much of the predictive burden are already present in prior Lumenary records: Method's Reckoning, Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, and related entry and support ledgers. External prior art also strongly anticipates the components: Asad and Lindbeck for native authority and grammar, Sharf and Katz-style contextualism for suspicion of experience-first comparison, Hori for Zen training and verification, Pargament for agency distribution, VCE for multidimensional contemplative difficulty coding, MN 22 for validated-then-released method, Heart Sutra for no-attainment plus reliance, Tannisho for Other Power custody, and Dogen for practice-realization anomaly. The surviving value is a bounded split-source interaction test, not a doctrine candidate or strong original discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:129:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, practice-realization, retained method, released method, self-undermining method, embodied method, radical Other Power, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, community-held, Prajnaparamita-held, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, inherited practice, apophatic refusal, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:130:- Compare predictive value against Asad discursive tradition, Lindbeck grammar, Weberian authority, Sharf and Katz contextualism, Pargament agency styles, upaya pedagogy, VCE variables, institution type, teacher style, social ecology, clinical risk, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:132:- Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.
findings/convergences/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self-scoring.md:1:# Dialogue Convergence: Whether the gate can reliably distinguish bypassing from compulsive self-scoring...
findings/convergences/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self-scoring.md:13:Whether the gate can reliably distinguish bypassing from compulsive self-scoring in the moment, and whether people whose wound is self-evaluation can safely self-administer that gate without turning the repair into another score.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:26:- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:29:Structural observation: SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the five aggregates, yet the discourse depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and a sequence from seeing to disenchantment and release. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 refuses ordinary objectification of the seer and knower, but authorizes the remainder as the inner ruler and Self. Tannisho relocates efficacy away from self-power into Amida's vow and entrusting, while also preserving teacher lineage, warning against license, and refusing ownership of disciples. Mahasi's Manual of Insight makes operational remainder unusually explicit: ethical preparation, concentration, noting, progress mapping, teacher interpretation, and verification are all part of the practice surface. The close read supports the three variables, but also shows that much of the structure is already visible in primary materials.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:31:Secondary literature gap: This audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully reread Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Wilber, Engler's full chapter context, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen and Mahamudra manuals, or Britton's full adverse-effects corpus. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Burmese terms were not checked directly. Stronger novelty would require split-source coding and practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:41:- religious coping self-directing deferring collaborative Pargament agency styles
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:47:- Tannisho Other Power self-power calculation warning license
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:57:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for distributing agency and control across self, deity, collaboration, deferral, and surrender, with practical consequences for coping.; difference: Pargament is not focused on contemplative negation or verification after self-dissolution.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The support-locus and gift-effort categories need baseline comparison against religious coping styles.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:65:Unlike VCE, Britton's adverse-effects work, Engler, Pargament, Lindbeck, Asad, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating contemplative paths can be coded along three independent axes, operational capacity, residue policy, and training ecology, and that the interaction among those axes will predict safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns better than any one axis alone.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:69:Candidate: Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited devotional practice, radical Other Power, and secular mindfulness adverse effects strain the model from different sides.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:71:Why it strains the model: Practice-realization can refuse a before-and-after account in which capacity remains and then receives a residue label. Inherited practice may work through ritual and community before explicit doctrine is understood. Other Power can treat naming receptivity as a capacity as a self-power distortion. Secular mindfulness adverse effects can occur without explicit self-negating residue policy, which may mean ecology, dose, arousal, vulnerability, and interpretation explain more than the proposed residue axis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:80:- If: Training ecology moderates the risk created by capacity and residue mismatch. Then: High-intensity, low-supervision, weak-community settings should produce more adverse or confused reports when operational demands are high and residue policy is easily misunderstood. Weakens if: Ecology does not moderate outcomes after controlling for baseline vulnerability and practice dose, or mismatch cases do not show distinct repair needs. Test surface: Retreat adverse-event datasets, Cheetah House style case intake data, and prospective Lumenary practice-seed safety tracking.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:88:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:96:- Does the model predict safeguards or repairs you would not already derive from upaya, spiritual materialism, trauma-informed care, religious coping, or ordinary teacher experience?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:120:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The idea is useful and testable, but its main components are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary ledgers, VCE and Cheetah House style adverse-effects research, Engler's functional ego warning, Pargament's agency and coping styles, Lindbeck's grammar model, Asad's discursive-tradition account, upaya capacity pedagogy, and primary-text evidence. The remaining contribution is a clearer three-factor interaction hypothesis and a split-source testing protocol.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:127:- Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, inherited practice, no-threshold practice, Other Power refusal, grace-held support, teacher-recognition support, secular extraction, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:128:- Compare predictive power against VCE influencing factors, Cheetah House adverse-event categories, Engler's developmental warning, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck grammar, Asad discursive tradition, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:31:      "test_surface": "Coded comparison of SN 45.8, Shinran letters and Tannisho, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho materials, Dogen Bendowa, and contemporary lineage manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:41:      "expected_observation": "Gift practice distorted into agency produces anxious self-checking or pride. Direct introduction without stabilization produces reification, distraction, or antinomian confidence. Effort practice without memory or reflexivity produces mechanical repetition or bypassing.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:51:    "Shinran Other Power self power calculation entrusting practitioner capacity",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:55:    "spiritual bypassing trauma no-self mindfulness Engler Welwood"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:65:      "difference": "Engler does not split the requirement into five scored load categories or compare Other Power, right effort, Dzogchen, and practice-realization as load distributions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:96:    "Rename practitioner capacity as functional support locus when auditing Other Power, grace, and Dzogchen, so the model does not smuggle self-power into traditions that reject it.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:98:    "Code primary manuals before using broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho, Shinran letters, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa, and one Advaita prerequisite text.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:105:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is just Engler, Upaya, adhikara, two truths, ordinary pedagogy, or Shinran's self-power versus Other Power distinction in new vocabulary. Pure Land or Dzogchen teachers say the model misdescribes their decisive moment by making it a human capacity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:126:      "Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:128:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model may smuggle self-power back into Shinran by treating entrusting as a practitioner capacity. It may also psychologize Dzogchen recognition as a personal skill rather than primordial awareness recognizing itself. The safer formulation is that paths require functional support loci, not necessarily capacities owned by the practitioner.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:129:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Search found very close prior art in Engler's ego-strength-before-no-self thesis, Buddhist personhood debates, Pudgalavada arguments about karma and liberation, Buddhist functional-self and self-pattern theory, Upaya as capacity-sensitive pedagogy, spiritual bypassing literature, and Lumenary's prior audited idea Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves. I did not find an exact five-column gift-effort ledger with relocation rules across Pure Land, Dzogchen, right effort, and practice-realization, but the main architecture was already specified in the prior Lumenary audit's next-loop instruction.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.json:130:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 strongly supports the agency side of the ledger: right effort requires desire, striving, energy, applied mind, and maintenance across wholesome and unwholesome states. Shinran's Letter to Senshin sharply resists that grammar by denying calculative working on the practicer's side and placing settlement in Other Power. The ledger is useful because it notices the contrast, but the phrase receiving capacity is not simply textual in Shinran. The text more nearly says that the decisive settling is not possessed by the practitioner. Longchen Rabjam's Trekcho instruction, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction, supports the relocation pattern by rejecting contrived effort while still requiring recognition of what has been introduced, undistracted abiding, vows, devotion, renunciation, and post-meditation conduct."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Blind coders using only entry texts should predict later warning profiles, such as pride warnings in self-effort paths, passivity warnings in grace or Other Power paths, and teacher-dependence warnings in recognition-based paths, above baseline models.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:56:    "Pargament religious problem solving styles self-directing deferring collaborative",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:61:    "Shinran Other Power self power Primal Vow Name",
