reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:110:      "overlap": "Very close for relocating decisive practice and beginning to Other Power, the Name, and the Primal Vow rather than self-owned effort.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:111:      "source": "Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:130:    "Run baseline comparisons against Rambo conversion stages, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck grammar, liminality, legitimate peripheral participation, scaffolding, upaya, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:135:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.70 to about 0.55. The layered beginning structure is strongly anticipated by Rambo conversion theory, liminality, situated learning, scaffolding, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Berger plausibility structures, Shinran Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, and prior Lumenary entry-claimant records. The remaining contribution is an extension: a split-corpus coding protocol that asks whether affordance, institutional selection, authorization grammar, and handoff density predict warnings and repair episodes without circular evidence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:148:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:160:      "Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:164:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Search covered conversion-stage theory, religious coping agency styles, plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, doctrine-as-grammar, scaffolding, Shinran Other Power, Tannisho, SN 45.8, and Soto practice-realization. It did not fully close-read Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, Calvinist and Wesleyan entry sermons, Gelug lamrim texts, Sufi bayah sources, or psychotherapy alliance literature. That gap blocks candidate-discovery status.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:165:    "structural_observation": "Tannisho layers beginning through entrusting, Amida's Primal Vow, teacher humility, and a refusal to claim disciples or self-owned merit. SN 45.8 layers the path through trainable functions: view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The contrast supports the candidate's agency-authorization intuition, but it also shows that the strongest pieces are already visible in primary texts and prior Lumenary entry-claimant work."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning-8a8d544ce3b6f17a.json:174:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo's conversion stages, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's religious agency styles, Lave and Wenger's situated learning, liminality theory, scaffolding theory, Shinran's Other Power grammar, and prior Lumenary entry-claimant work, this idea says beginning should be coded as four separable layers: empirical affordance, institutional selection, normative agency authorization, and repeated handoff density. Its possible contribution is not that beginnings are layered, but that these layers can be split into independent corpora and tested for prediction of warnings, repair instructions, and reauthorization episodes."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:194:      "argument": "Codex's challenge lands cleanly: the original model does not separate what caused entry from what the tradition later authorizes as a legitimate account of entry. I accept the two-layer split as necessary and overdue. I also concede that universality must go; the model applies where entry is thematized as a problem, not everywhere. But the separation of layers does not reduce the model to mere narrative analysis. The grammar is not only retrospective. It is active at the point of guidance: it shapes what teachers say to newcomers, what they warn against, what evidence they accept for genuine entry, and what they diagnose as premature or self-deceived. A Jodo Shinshu teacher who hears 'I worked hard to develop trust' will respond differently from a Theravada teacher who hears the same sentence, not because they are applying different retrospective labels to a completed event, but because their grammar identifies different dangers in the act of beginning. The Shinshu teacher hears self-power contaminating other-power trust. The Theravada teacher hears healthy effort following encounter. The grammar constitutes the guidance encounter, not merely the story told about it afterward. Taylor's social imaginary argument and Taves's work on 'deemed special' attributions support this: the available interpretive framework partly constitutes the experience, not only its narration. A practitioner formed within Shinran's grammar may genuinely experience the arising of trust as something that arrived rather than something they produced, because the grammar shaped the attentional categories within which the experience occurred. This does not mean the grammar is a complete causal account. It means the two layers (lived mechanism and authorized grammar) are not fully independent. The grammar is one of the variables that shapes the mechanism, alongside crisis, social context, institutional pressure, personality, and the other factors Rambo identifies. The revised model therefore makes a more modest but more testable claim: first-break grammar predicts distinguishable pastoral consequences at the entry point: different safeguards, different warnings, different evidence requirements, different characteristic errors. This is not a universal structural constraint on all contemplative paths. It is a variable that matters most where entry is experienced as blocked, and it matters most to the cohort of people for whom beginning is the problem: those in depression, addiction, burnout, grief, meaning-crisis, or the trap of achievement-contingent worth, where the demand for self-generated initiative reproduces the condition it is meant to cure. The crux is whether the grammar is active enough to produce these distinguishable consequences after controlling for the variables Codex rightly names: conversion process, institutional authority, teacher personality, cultural context, and retrospective narrative training. The proposed test (identical case vignettes presented to teachers from different traditions, with guidance coded independently of the typology) would settle this. If guidance clusters by first-break grammar, the model survives as a predictive tool. If it clusters by other variables, the model should be reduced to a taxonomy of entry narratives, still useful for comparative scholarship but no longer claiming to predict practice architecture.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:212:      "defense": "The challenge is right that retrospective grammar and causal mechanism must be separated. But the separation does not defeat the model; it clarifies what the model actually predicts. The revised claim is that first-break grammar is causally active at the guidance layer: it shapes what teachers tell newcomers, what dangers they name, what evidence they accept for genuine entry, and what they warn against as premature or self-deceived. This is not a retreat to mere sociology. Pastoral guidance is where tradition meets the practitioner's lived confusion, and the grammar determines the shape of that meeting.\n\nConsider the safeguard prediction concretely. A Jodo Shinshu teacher encountering someone who says 'I worked hard to develop trust in Amida' will hear this as a warning sign: self-powered effort to produce other-power trust is the characteristic entry error. A Theravada teacher hearing 'I worked hard to develop faith in the teacher' will hear this as healthy. The grammar does not merely redescribe a completed entry; it actively shapes what the teacher does next, what corrections they offer, and what the practitioner is encouraged to notice or abandon. The grammar is constitutive of the guidance encounter, not decorative.\n\nTaylor's social imaginary argument supports this: the available framework of meaning partly constitutes what experiences are possible, not only how they are narrated afterward. A practitioner formed by Shinran's grammar may genuinely experience the arising of trust as something that happened to them, not because they are retrospectively redescribing self-generated effort, but because the grammar shaped the attentional field within which the experience occurred. A practitioner formed by Theravada's grammar may genuinely experience their encounter with a teacher as the critical break, because the tradition trained them to notice that encounter as significant.\n\nThis means the two layers (lived mechanism and authorized grammar) are not fully independent. The grammar partly constitutes the mechanism by shaping attention, expectation, and the categories available for noticing what is happening. The model does not need the grammar to be a complete causal account of entry. It needs the grammar to be active enough that different grammars produce distinguishable guidance, distinguishable safeguards, and distinguishable characteristic errors at the point of entry. That is an empirical claim, and it can be tested.\n\nThe human problem the model addresses is real and specific. People experiencing depression, addiction, burnout, meaning-crisis, or achievement-contingent self-worth often face a version of the first-break problem: they cannot begin the process that would help them because the condition itself blocks beginning. Therapy requires enough clarity to cooperate with therapy. Recovery requires enough stability to show up. Contemplative practice requires enough stillness to sit. The model does not claim to solve this problem, but it names the structural options available: someone else breaks the circle for you (social encounter, therapist, sponsor), something beyond your control initiates the process (grace, surrender, medication), or the capacity was never absent and only needs conditions for recognition (self-disclosure, the moment of clarity). These are not only doctrinal positions; they are pastoral strategies with different consequences for how helpers approach people who are stuck.\n\nThe cohort is blocked seekers, cross-tradition practitioners navigating incompatible entry assumptions, pastoral counselors and therapists working with people who cannot begin, and comparative scholars building structural models of contemplative architecture. The non-fit case is people for whom entry was never a problem: those formed by inherited practice, family ritual, cultural immersion, or ordinary socialization, where the path was always already underway before the question of beginning could arise.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:224:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:265:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:27:- MN 22 raft simile, Heart Sutra no attainment, and Dogen practice-realization, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:29:Structural observation: Zhuangzi and MN 22 both support release of a tool after its work is done, but they presuppose a real catch or crossing. MN 22 also stresses proper grasp before release, which prevents premature quitting. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, so no-attainment is not simple inactivity. Dogen strains the model most, because practice and realization are inseparable, which blocks a universal before-and-after completion rule. These primary texts support a scoped after-use discipline, not the broad claim that finishing is always the next virtue.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.md:105:Prediction: Teams with high start rates and low completion rates will reduce duplicate tickets, abandoned drafts, and rework when action-state gates are enforced before new creation.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:7:Status: draft
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:42:- Dogen practice-realization beginner original enlightenment Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:53:- Dogen practice-realization sources, for example Soto and Bendowa summaries, https://zenlineage.org/schools/soto and https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/: overlap: The temporal-collapse strategy is already central to Dogen's practice-realization, where practice is not merely a means to later awakening.; difference: It does not compare this strategy against Advaita, Theravada, and Sufi models of self-continuity.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The Zen strategy is known; the comparative placement may still be useful.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:69:- If: The stronger a path's final self-dissolution claim, the more explicit its safeguards should be against premature or distorted self-loss. Then: Manuals and teachers should warn against nihilism, dissociation, spiritual bypassing, false attainment, antinomianism, or ego-inflation in ways that match the path's self-management strategy. Weakens if: Warnings show no relationship to self-teaching and track only institution, teacher personality, or general ethics. Test surface: Coded comparison of Theravada, Zen, Dzogchen, Advaita, Sufi, Christian apophatic, and Pure Land training materials.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:92:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners find that the rubric predicts real training differences and clarifies why premature self-dissolution, clinging to witness, bypassing, or false surrender fail differently across paths.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning-704d17e4307ae461.md:22:- Thinking method source: MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, used as disciplined non-attachment to methods: trust a method enough to cross, then test whether grasping it creates distortion.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:25:- Shinran, Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:27:Structural observation: SN 45.8 makes right effort operational and practitioner-facing: desire, endeavor, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities are all assigned to the monk's practice field. Tannisho reverses the claimant grammar: nembutsu is not a practice or good act when it arises from Other Power, and claims such as my disciples are rejected because the working belongs to Amida. The comparison supports a real difference in claimant policy, but Tannisho is not a late handoff after training. It often refuses self-claim from the entrance, so the model needs a no-transfer or analyst-frame-refused value.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:29:Secondary literature gap: The search found close prior structures in religious coping styles, self-power and other-power, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Engler on ego strength before no-self, the Buddhist raft and upaya pattern, and local Lumenary capacity-ledger and credit-distribution work. I did not find the exact field list as a cross-tradition coding sheet, but the core agency-allocation and means-end reversal are well established.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:35:- Pargament self-directing deferring collaborative religious coping styles problem solving responsibility God
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:36:- Steve Bein Self Power Other Power and Non-Dualism in Japanese Buddhism
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:37:- Shinran Tannisho chapter 1 nembutsu mind arises Amida working
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:40:- Buddhist raft parable abandon teachings MN 22 upaya
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:46:- Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles, summarized at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/ and https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Very close for allocating responsibility among self, God, and collaboration. This already formalizes who carries agency and how responsibility is distributed.; difference: The candidate adds stage-level transfer, contemplative manuals, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair fields rather than measuring coping style in stress response.; novelty impact: High reduction. The main variable is not new, though the manual-coding form may extend it.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:47:- Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-Dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO: overlap: Very close for treating self-power, other-power, and non-dualism as structured alternatives rather than a simple binary.; difference: The candidate generalizes beyond Japanese Buddhism and asks where the transfer occurs for each trained function.; novelty impact: High reduction for the effort-gift architecture, moderate reduction for stage-sensitive coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:48:- Shinran, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/: overlap: Near exact for forbidden claimant language. The nembutsu is said to arise from Other Power, and even disciple ownership is rejected.; difference: Tannisho is a primary instance, not a comparative rubric. It may actually break the model by refusing the idea that a human function is first trained and then handed off.; novelty impact: High reduction and a major anomaly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:51:- MN 22, Alagaddūpama Sutta, raft parable, https://suttacentral.net/mn22/en/bodhi: overlap: Close for a method or teaching that must not be possessed after its work is done.; difference: The raft model is about non-clinging to the Dhamma after crossing, not a full transfer ledger of capacities, support holders, and repair practices.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the handoff-after-use pattern.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:57:Unlike Pargament, self-power and other-power debates, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary credit models, this idea says the decisive unit is a timed transfer for each required function, with observable safeguards and repairs at that transfer point.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:61:Candidate: Radical Jodo Shinshu, especially Tannisho chapters 8 and 10, where nembutsu is not the practitioner's practice or good act and no working is true working.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:71:- If: The handoff rubric should add predictive value beyond Pargament-style responsibility allocation and the local capacity ledger. Then: Two practices with the same broad credit type but different transfer timing show different safeguards and repair instructions. Weakens if: Support locus and credit-distribution coding predict the same outcomes without needing handoff timing. Test surface: Inter-rater coding of matched pairs such as Soto and Dzogchen, Pure Land and Christian grace, Theravada and karma-yoga.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.53 to about 0.44. The rubric is generative, but its parts are heavily anticipated by religious coping styles, self-power and other-power discourse, Dogen, Dzogchen manuals, the raft and upaya pattern, Engler, and local Lumenary priors. Treat as a consolidation unless inter-rater coding shows new predictive value.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:117:- Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa or Dogen practice-realization sources, and one Christian grace manual.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:25:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:28:Structural observation: MN 22 is a direct release template: the Dhamma is used for crossing and then not carried. The Heart Sutra complicates release because it denies path and attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, mantra, recitation, and teacher-mediated practice. Dogen complicates both retention and abandonment because practice and realization are described as one, so there is no clean after-stage where custody is decided.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before any public claim, read fuller work on upaya, raft and ladder metaphors, Wittgenstein's ladder, Nagarjuna's no-thesis claim, Hori on koan pedagogy, Sells on apophasis, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Dogen scholarship, Shinran scholarship, and Pargament on religious agency styles. Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, and Chinese terms were not checked here.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:36:- MN 22 raft simile Dhamma raft crossing not holding on primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:38:- Dogen Bendowa shusho itto practice realization one primary source
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:43:- Pargament religious problem solving styles self directing collaborative deferring
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:48:- Internal Lumenary audit, The Road Must Know Its End, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json: overlap: Extremely close. The prior audit already names keep, release, and embody as an after-use rubric and lowers novelty for the same MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen, Sells, Smith, and achievement-pressure basis.; difference: This candidate states the two axes more explicitly and frames the issue as method shape rather than road completion.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. This is mostly a renamed or slightly sharpened version of the existing Lumenary after-use model.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:50:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm: overlap: The raft simile already gives the core post-use structure: use the teaching for crossing, then do not carry it as a burden.; difference: The candidate generalizes this into a comparative typology and adds retained and embodied cases.; novelty impact: Downgrades the release quadrant to known primary-text structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:57:Unlike MN 22, Wittgenstein's ladder, Smith's Nagarjuna-Wittgenstein therapy, Sells's apophatic unsaying, Dogen's practice-realization, and prior Lumenary after-use models, this idea's possible contribution is a bounded coding rubric that tests whether method type predicts held-out warnings, repairs, and post-insight temptations in achievement-pressured practitioners.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:61:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization, Shinran Other Power, and the Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-reliance pattern.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:69:- If: Method shape predicts aftermath instruction. Then: Blind coders can code validates versus undermines and retained versus abandoned versus embodied from instruction passages, then predict held-out warnings, repairs, and verification rules better than tradition label alone. Weakens if: Coders cannot agree on the axes, or the axes do not predict held-out warnings better than generic variables such as teacher style, institution, practice intensity, or tradition identity. Test surface: Split-source corpus coding across MN 22, Heart Sutra, Mandukya, Dogen, Shinran, apophatic Christian, Sufi, Advaita, and koan-training sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:76:- Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22 and upaya
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:91:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is standard raft teaching, upaya, integration, surrender, practice-realization, or supervision in new language, and that the rubric does not change sequencing or repair.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.68 to 0.26. The core structure is already present in internal Lumenary records and in external raft, ladder, apophatic, therapeutic, and practice-realization sources. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it serves achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, burnout, and compulsive self-improvement among functioning practitioners. It is not a fit for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, or structural burnout where workload and material conditions are primary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If Eihei Shingi, Soto training, Shinran's cautions against licensed evil, nembutsu practice, and community transmission all function as retained disciplines with real effects, then non-instrumentality is not outside the custody apparatus. It is a different custody location: form-held, vow-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, or community-held."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:13:    "Shinran's Other Power denies practicer calculation and owned efficacy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Before asking what a practice does with authority over its result, ask whether it claims to produce a separable result at all. Custody, release, and correction vocabulary applies only to instrumental practices. Dogen's practice-realization and Shinran's Other Power dissolve the tool frame because sitting or entrusting is not owned as a means to a later product.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:31:      "test_surface": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, koan curricula, Advaita inquiry, apophatic Christian sources, Sufi fana and baqa, and ritual manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:51:    "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power practicer",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:52:    "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act Other Power self power",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:53:    "MN 22 raft simile instrumental practice crossing let go",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:58:    "Pargament religious problem solving styles agency God control"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:64:      "overlap": "Extremely close. The prior audit already says keep, release, embody assumes practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and that Shinran and Dogen break those assumptions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:80:      "difference": "The candidate uses Shinran as a non-tool boundary case rather than as Pure Land doctrine alone.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:82:      "overlap": "Very close. Shinran explicitly rejects practicer calculation and describes Other Power as no working, which undermines self-owned method efficacy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:83:      "source": "Shinran, On Jinen Honi, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:98:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and control attribution, not whether a practice produces a separable result.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:99:      "novelty_impact": "For Shinran-style agency relocation, novelty is low unless the separable-result gate predicts warnings beyond agency-style variables.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:101:      "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:108:    "Read non-instrumental ritual theory, autotelic flow literature, MacIntyre on practices, Dogen's Eihei Shingi, Bendowa and Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho in stronger translations before public use.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:111:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.34. The instrumental versus non-instrumental distinction is old and appears directly in Dogen, Shinran, ritual theory, autotelic activity theory, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits. The useful extension is narrower: using separable-result as a pre-coding scope gate for Lumenary's custody and release apparatus. Human-condition fit is strong for functioning perfectionists, founders, students, creators, and professionals who convert every activity into proof of worth. It is not for under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, severe depression, dissociation, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, coercive workloads, or people who need concrete completed outcomes restored before resultless practice is safe.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:114:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners and scholars say this is already standard as practice-realization, Other Power, autotelic ritual, internal goods, non-attachment, grace, or non-gaining mind, and that the scope gate adds no predictive guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:125:      "Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:135:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:136:      "Dogen shusho itto and Shinran jinen honi, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:138:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Non-instrumental self-description does not mean absence of discipline, correction, warnings, institutional form, or effects. Dogen still requires continuous practice, and Shinran still has nembutsu, entrusting, and cautions. The model may confuse no owned result with no practical structure.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:139:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit did not read Eihei Shingi, full Bendowa or Genjokoan in Japanese, Shinran's Japanese around jinen and hakarai, Tannisho anti-license passages in Japanese, ritual theory in depth, Aristotle praxis and poiesis sources, or empirical studies of autotelic practice and perfectionism. These are necessary before raising novelty.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:140:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is explicitly instrumental: effort with the raft gets one across, then the raft should not be carried. Dogen's shusho itto demolishes the cause-effect separation between practice and realization, while Shinran's jinen honi removes calculation by the practicer and locates efficacy in Other Power. The contrast supports a scope distinction, but not a discovery: the instrumental versus non-instrumental contrast is already structurally visible in the primary texts."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json:152:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Dogen's practice-realization, Shinran's Other Power, autotelic activity theory, non-instrumental ritual theory, MacIntyre's internal goods, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits, this idea's possible contribution is a practical scope gate for comparative coding: ask first whether a practice claims to produce a separable result before applying custody, release, or correction vocabulary."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:27:- Tannisho, sections VII to IX, translated by Taitetsu Unno, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:29:Structural observation: SN 45.8 reads like a high-agency ledger: right view knows suffering and cessation, right resolve is directed toward renunciation and harmlessness, right effort generates desire and persistence, right mindfulness maintains ardent attention, and right concentration stabilizes the path. Tannisho VIII reverses the ownership grammar: nembutsu is not the practitioner's practice or good act because it is Other Power and free of self-power. Tannisho IX treats lack of joy not as simple incapacity but as blind passion already anticipated by the vow. The pair supports the vector insight because similar path functions are assigned different direction and locus. It also threatens the model because calling entrusting a capacity may already distort Shinran's grammar.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit searched Pargament, Engler, Hadot, Ferrer, Katz, Sharf, Dahl, Lutz, Davidson, Lindahl, Britton, upaya literature, Tannisho, Bendowa, and SN 45.8. It did not close-read Shinran's letters, Kyogyoshinsho, Longchenpa, Wangchuk Dorje, Christian grace manuals, Sufi fana and baqa texts, or original Pali and Japanese terms. That gap blocks any candidate-discovery claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:37:- Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles of coping self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:48:- Tannisho chapter 8 nembutsu not practice good act self power calculation other power translation Unno PDF
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:49:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization enlightenment are one text translation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:54:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Very close for locus and direction. Pargament already distinguishes self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious problem-solving styles by the relationship between person and God, and ties those styles to competence and religiousness.; difference: Pargament studies coping and divine-human problem solving, not a cross-tradition ledger of receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration across soteriologies.; novelty impact: High reduction. The vector ledger must prove it predicts more than agency locus and divine involvement.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:62:- Shinran and Tannisho on Other Power, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf and practitioner summary, https://tricycle.org/article/self-power-and-other-power/: overlap: Very close for load relocation and forbidden self-claiming. Tannisho explicitly denies that nembutsu is the practitioner's self-powered practice or good act.; difference: Tannisho is one primary path grammar, not a comparative model. It may be better treated as an anomaly than as support.; novelty impact: High reduction and high anomaly pressure. The candidate must avoid recoding gift as practitioner-owned capacity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:66:Unlike Pargament, Engler, Dahl, Hadot, Ferrer, Katz, Sharf, upaya theory, and Shinran, this idea claims that path requirements can be coded as a reusable vector ledger where each functional role has magnitude, direction, locus, stage, safeguards, and failure mode, and that whole-path soteriology may generate the direction of each role. Its possible contribution is predictive rubric design, not the discovery that traditions differ in agency, capacity, or context.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:70:Candidate: Dogen's Bendowa practice-realization, especially the claim that training and enlightenment are not two, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:78:- If: Capacity direction is generated by soteriology rather than only by practice technique. Then: Independent coders should infer later manual warnings and safeguards from early claims about self, liberation, and final transformation at above-chance rates. For example, Other Power texts should warn against calculation, practice-realization texts should warn against treating practice as a means to a later goal, and deconstructive paths should warn against reification and dissociation. Weakens if: Scalar maturity, broad tradition labels, or Pargament-style agency locus predict the same warnings as well as the vector ledger, or coders cannot agree on direction and locus. Test surface: Blind coding trial across SN 45.8, Tannisho, Bendowa, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra manual, one Christian grace manual, and one Sufi fana or baqa source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:81:- If: Gift and recognition traditions still have observable conditions, but those conditions will not be best described as practitioner-owned capacities. Then: Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, and Christian grace teachers should accept some functional preconditions while objecting to capacity ownership language. Their corrections should cluster around vow-held, teacher-held, grace-held, recognition-event, and analyst-frame-refused values. Weakens if: Teachers either accept ordinary capacity language without reservation, or reject all functional precondition coding while still showing no predictable teaching safeguards. Test surface: Practitioner-scholar interviews and manual coding of Shinran, pointing-out instructions, and grace texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:86:- Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:96:- Does directionality predict actual sequencing, warnings, and repair instructions for students, or is it obvious under older terms such as upaya, grace, self-power, Other Power, or ego development?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:101:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is standard upaya, religious coping, contemplative-development theory, spiritual bypassing caution, cultural-linguistic theology, or ordinary lineage pedagogy. They also say the ledger does not change teaching choices or predict failures better than existing teacher judgment.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.70 to about 0.61. The scalar-to-vector move is useful, but its parts are strongly anticipated by Pargament's agency styles, Engler's developmental prerequisites, Dahl and Lutz's meditation mechanism taxonomies, VCE adverse-effect variables, Hadot's spiritual exercises, Ferrer's participatory pluralism, Katz and Sharf's contextualism, Buddhist upaya, and Shinran's Other Power. The remaining contribution is a promising operational synthesis with testable predictions, not a discovered law of spiritual paths.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:128:- Close-read Shinran's Tannisho and letters, SN 45.8, Bendowa or Genjokoan, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, one Christian grace text, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before public use.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.md:130:- Run an inter-rater trial comparing the vector ledger against scalar capacity, Pargament agency styles, and VCE-style practice, practitioner, relationship, and context variables.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The strongest prior art is Pargament's self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious coping; Christian monergism and synergism; Japanese Buddhist jiriki and tariki; Sri Vaishnava markata and marjara; Sufi maqam and hal; and religious-attribution or God-control psychology. The searched literature did not show the exact five-type typology with activity-centered and ground-centered categories plus failure-mode predictions, but the main agency-allocation variable is well established.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:37:- Pargament religious coping self directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:44:- Dogen practice realization one Bendowa Advaita attainment already attained
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:48:- Pargament et al., religious coping styles, accessible summary at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/: overlap: Very close. The self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already formalize whether problem-solving responsibility rests in the person, God, or both.; difference: Credit distribution broadens from coping to contemplative and soteriological practice, adds activity-centered and ground-centered types, and predicts tradition-specific safeguards.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. The core variable is known under religious coping and control allocation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:50:- Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-Dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO: overlap: Close. Bein already treats self-power, other-power, and non-dualism as a philosophical variable inside Japanese Buddhism.; difference: The candidate generalizes beyond Japanese Buddhism and adds failure-mode and safeguard predictions.; novelty impact: High reduction, especially for the three core categories of practitioner, source, and nondual credit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:59:Unlike Pargament, monergism and synergism, self-power and other-power, and markata and marjara debates, this idea adds activity-centered and ground-centered patterns, treats credit attribution as a felt practice variable, and predicts matching failure modes and safeguards across multiple traditions.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:86:- Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament and locus-of-control research
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:89:- Is this five-type credit model more than self-power versus other-power, grace versus works, monergism versus synergism, and Pargament's coping styles?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:93:Answers that reduce originality: Experts say the typology is already contained in self-power and other-power, monergism and synergism, prapatti debates, maqam and hal, or Pargament. Practitioners say failure modes are not type-specific or that tradition-level typing is misleading.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.48. The five-type comparative frame is generative, but the main structure is anticipated by Pargament's religious coping styles, God-control attribution research, Christian monergism and synergism, Japanese self-power and other-power, Sri Vaishnava prapatti debates, Sufi station-state distinctions, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary work.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:118:- Read Pargament's original religious problem-solving work and God-attribution literature before any novelty claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:37:Risk of overread: High. The model risks treating texts, teacher norms, report vocabulary, actual phenomenology, and embodied habit as one process. It also risks making every difference count as grain and every doctrinal sentence count as residue policy. Traditions such as Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence may reject the developmental sequence or the analyst's residue vocabulary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:73:Candidate: Successful dual-trained or hybrid practitioners who switch methods smoothly after clear instruction, plus traditions that refuse the analyst's developmental sequence, especially Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:139:- Add mandatory anomaly values: no-threshold, practice-realization, direct recognition, radical Other Power, grace-held support, inherited practice, successful dual practice, no-residue report, secular extraction, psychiatric vulnerability, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:26:- MN 22 raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html; Heart Sutra no attainment with retained reliance, https://www.fgsitc.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Heart-Sutra-2016.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:27:- Zhuangzi fish trap and words, https://ctext.org/zhuangzi/what-comes-from-without; Dogen Genjokoan practice-realization, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 and Zhuangzi support releasing a tool after it has done its work, but both presuppose that the work really has been done. The Heart Sutra keeps reliance after denying attainment, so not every repeated form is clinging. Dogen sharply strains the claim because ongoing expression of realization can require repeated practice without a separate product. Primary texts therefore support a narrow anti-duplication rule only where a restatement adds no new source, anomaly, prediction, or conduct change.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:63:Candidate: Legitimate repetition: liturgy, zazen, nembutsu, deliberate teaching restatement, iterative writing, independent convergence, and hard research that needs multiple framings before the real variable appears.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:73:- If: The Duplicate Check helps high-output overproducers but not under-producers. Then: Screened high-output participants show fewer redundant drafts and more concrete actions after four uses, without higher shame, rumination, or reduced genuinely new work. Weakens if: The prompt increases avoidance, shame, or underproduction, or ordinary WIP limits and planning prompts perform equally well. Test surface: Two-week pilot with WIP count, duplicate-output coding, action completion, rumination, shame, burnout, and novelty measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:104:Structural translation: A repeated idea becomes an issue, ticket, manuscript, or design draft with a recorded next action. Starting a new version is blocked until audit, merge, review, release, or explicit reopen criteria are satisfied.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-restating-is-not-realizing-1ed7e902d1f20ee6.md:106:Prediction: Teams using a duplicate-check gate will show fewer duplicate tickets, fewer parallel drafts of the same argument, shorter review queues, and more completed merges, without fewer genuinely novel tickets.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:177:      "crux_assessment": "The current evidence already leans toward revision because MN 22, Rinzai koan curriculum, Heart Sutra reliance, and direct-introduction systems all retain some method after undermining method-ownership. The three types are clearest as recurring moves, not as stable boxes.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:179:      "fairness_check": "The idea already names its best anomaly: validated-then-abandoned hybrids. It also does not overclaim final doctrine status, since it remains a draft model with explicit textual, interpretive, phenomenological, analogical, and speculative labels.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:181:      "new_source": "Shinran's Tannisho and Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling complicate the completion model because they move the decisive authority problem to the entrance, not the end. Hearing, saying, and entrusting remain human-facing, while calculation is forbidden from the practitioner's side from the start.",
