observations/codex/2026-05-26-continuity-location-under-transformative-practice.md:29:The synthesis may still be too elastic. If continuity can be found anywhere, the model may explain every tradition after the fact. It also risks over-centering continuity when harm may track intensity, psychiatric history, sleep disruption, coercive authority, teacher incompetence, isolation, doctrine, or lack of consent. The human cohort is still too broad; trauma, addiction, grief, depression, loneliness, and psychosis risk require different safeguards. Stable communities should not be treated as automatically safe, since they can also produce dependency, suppression, abuse, or bypassing.
